advanced:
@deva[अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम्] — a meaningful form, not @deva[धातु], not @deva[प्रत्यय], is @deva[प्रातिपदिक].

**Why @deva[अर्थवत्]?** @deva[वन्] in @deva[वनम्] has no meaning alone; if @deva[प्रातिपदिक], @ref[8.2.7] (@deva[नलोपः प्रातिपदिकान्तस्य]) would delete @deva[न्].

**Why @deva[अधातु]?** @deva[अहन्] (3sg impf of @deva[हन्])—@deva[न्] stays because it's verbal.

**Why @deva[अप्रत्यय]?** @deva[कुण्डे]—ends in @deva[इ] (locative); if @deva[प्रातिपदिक], @deva[ए] would shorten by @ref[1.2.47].

@deva[निपात] = @deva[प्रातिपदिक] per @deva[महाभाष्य]: @deva[अध्यागच्छति], @deva[प्रलम्बते].

standard:
Adjectives of @deva[लुप्]-derived words agree in gender and number, except when the noun is a @deva[जाति] (class word).

**Agreeing adjectives:**
@deva[पञ्चालाः रमणीयाः बह्वन्नाः बहुक्षीरघृताः] 'the pleasant @[pañcālas], rich in food, milk, and ghee'

**@deva[जाति] words don't trigger agreement:**
@deva[पञ्चालाः जनपदः] 'the @[pañcāla] country' — @deva[जनपद] is a class noun, so it takes its own gender/number.

Indirect qualifiers also don't agree:
@deva[पञ्चालाः जनपदो रमणीयो बह्वन्नः] — @deva[रमणीयः] qualifies @deva[जनपद], not @deva[पञ्चाल] directly.

**What is @deva[जाति]?** A word denoting a class by form, applicable to individuals without special instruction (@deva[आकृतिग्रहणाज्जातिर्लिङ्गानां च न सर्वभाक्]).

A feminine @deva[वृद्ध] word with a @deva[युवन्] undergoes @deva[एकशेष] and becomes masculine. This extends @ref[1.2.65].

**Examples:**
- @deva[गार्गी] (fem. gotra) + @deva[गार्ग्यायणः] (masc. yuvan) = @deva[गार्ग्यौ] (masc. dual)
- @deva[दाक्षी] + @deva[दाक्षायणः] = @deva[दाक्षौ]

The conditions from @ref[1.2.65] apply: the words must differ only in affix.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[स्त्री] in the @[sūtra] means @deva[वृद्धस्त्री]—the feminine form of the elder branch.}

advanced:
Feminine @deva[वृद्ध] + @deva[युवन्] → @deva[एकशेष], retained as masculine.

- @deva[गार्गी] + @deva[गार्ग्यायणः] → @deva[गार्ग्यौ] (masc.)
- @deva[दाक्षी] + @deva[दाक्षायणः] → @deva[दाक्षौ]

Conditions from @ref[1.2.65] apply (@deva[तल्लक्षणश्चेदेव विशेषः]).

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[स्त्री] = @deva[वृद्धस्त्री].}

@deva[धातु] = words denoting action, starting with @deva[भू]. Term predates @[pāṇini].

Ten @deva[गण]s: @deva[भ्वादि], @deva[अदादि], @deva[जुहोत्यादि], @deva[दिवादि], @deva[स्वादि], @deva[तुदादि], @deva[रुधादि], @deva[तनादि], @deva[क्र्यादि], @deva[चुरादि].

This @deva[अध्याय] primarily assigns @deva[परस्मैपद]/@deva[आत्मनेपद].

@deva[वा] is @deva[मङ्गलार्थ]—regular @deva[सन्धि] would give @deva[भ्वादि].

@deva[कर्तरि] + @deva[व्यतिहार] → @deva[आत्मनेपद].

- @deva[व्यतिपचन्ते] 'they cook for each other'
- @deva[व्यतिलुनते] 'he cuts (another's task)'

**No @deva[व्यतिहार]:** @deva[लुनन्ति].

@deva[व्यतिहार] and @deva[कर्तरि] continue through @ref[1.3.16]. @deva[कर्मन्] = action, not technical object.

standard:
After @deva[अनु]/@deva[सम्]/@deva[परि]/@deva[आ] + @deva[क्रीड्] 'to play,' @deva[आत्मनेपद]. The @deva[च] includes @deva[आङ्].

**Examples:**
- @deva[आक्रीडते], @deva[संक्रीडते], @deva[अनुक्रीडते], @deva[परिक्रीडते]

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[सम्] + @deva[क्रीड्] meaning 'creaking noise' is parasmaipada: @deva[संक्रीडन्ति शकटानि] 'the carts creak.'}

**Must be @deva[उपसर्ग], not @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय]:** @deva[माणवकमनुक्रीडति] 'he plays imitating the boy'—@deva[अनु] is @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] (@ref[1.4.83], @ref[2.3.8]), so parasmaipada.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Additional @[ātmanepada] rules: @deva[आ] + @deva[गम्] 'to wait for': @deva[आगमयस्व माणवकम्]; @deva[शिक्ष्] 'to inquire': @deva[विद्यासु शिक्षते]; @deva[नाथ्] 'to bless': @deva[सर्पिषो नाथते]; @deva[अनु] + @deva[हृ] 'to take after parents': @deva[पैतृकमश्वा अनुहरते]; @deva[अप] + @deva[कॄ] 'to scratch with joy': @deva[अपस्किरते वृषभो हृष्टः]; @deva[आ] + @deva[नु]/@deva[प्रच्छ्]: @deva[आनुते शृगालः], @deva[आपृच्छते गुरुम्]; @deva[शप्] 'to swear': @deva[देवदत्ताय शपते].}

advanced:
After @deva[अनु]/@deva[सम्]/@deva[परि]/@deva[आ] + @deva[क्रीड्], @deva[आत्मनेपद]. @deva[च] includes @deva[आङ्].

@deva[आक्रीडते], @deva[संक्रीडते], @deva[अनुक्रीडते], @deva[परिक्रीडते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[सम्] + @deva[क्रीड्] 'creaking' → parasmaipada: @deva[संक्रीडन्ति शकटानि].}

**@deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] blocks:** @deva[माणवकमनुक्रीडति] (see @ref[1.4.83], @ref[2.3.8]).

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Other @[ātmanepada]: @deva[आगमयस्व] 'wait'; @deva[शिक्षते] 'inquires'; @deva[नाथते] 'blesses'; @deva[अनुहरते] 'takes after'; @deva[अपस्किरते] 'scratches joyfully'; @deva[आनुते] 'howls'; @deva[आपृच्छते] 'asks'; @deva[शपते] 'swears.'}

After @deva[सम्]/@deva[अव]/@deva[प्र]/@deva[वि] + @deva[स्था], @deva[आत्मनेपद].

@deva[संतिष्ठते], @deva[अवतिष्ठते], @deva[प्रतिष्ठते], @deva[वितिष्ठते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[आ] + @deva[स्था] 'solemn declaration': @deva[आस्थास्ये].}

standard:
@deva[स्था] (without prefix) takes @deva[आत्मनेपद] when meaning @deva[प्रकाशन] (disclosing intentions) or @deva[स्थेयाख्य] (arbitration).

@deva[स्थेयाख्य] = @deva[स्थेय] (arbitrator) + @deva[आख्य] (name)

**Examples:**
- @deva[तिष्ठते जायापत्ये] 'the wife expresses her wish to the husband'
- @deva[त्वयि तिष्ठते] 'he refers to you for settlement'
- @deva[संशय्य कर्णादिषु तिष्ठते यः] 'who, when in doubt, has recourse to @[karṇa] as umpire'

After @deva[उद्] + @deva[स्था] (not meaning 'to rise from seat'), @deva[आत्मनेपद].

**@deva[आत्मनेपद] (@deva[ईहा] = effort):**
- @deva[गेहे उत्तिष्ठते] 'he strives for the house'
- @deva[कुटुम्बे उत्तिष्ठते] 'he exerts for family'

**@deva[परस्मैपद] (rising):**
- @deva[आसनादुत्तिष्ठति] 'he rises from seat'

@deva[कर्मन्] = action, not grammatical object.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[उद्] must express @deva[ईहा] (effort/desire). Without this sense: @deva[अस्माद्ग्रामात्शतमुत्तिष्ठति] 'a hundred is yielded from this village'—parasmaipada.}

advanced:
@deva[उद्] + @deva[स्था] (not 'rise from seat') → @deva[आत्मनेपद].

- @deva[गेहे उत्तिष्ठते], @deva[कुटुम्बे उत्तिष्ठते] (striving)
- @deva[आसनादुत्तिष्ठति] (rising—parasmaipada)

@deva[कर्मन्] = action. @note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[उद्] must express @deva[ईहा]: @deva[अस्माद्ग्रामात्शतमुत्तिष्ठति] (no @deva[ईहा]) → parasmaipada.}

standard:
After @deva[उप] + @deva[स्था] meaning 'to worship' (@deva[मन्त्रपूर्वकोपस्थान]), @deva[आत्मनेपद].

**@deva[आत्मनेपद]:**
- @deva[ऐन्द्र्या गार्हपत्यमुपतिष्ठते] 'he worships with @[aindrī] at @[gārhapatya]'

**@deva[परस्मैपद]:**
- @deva[भर्तारमुपतिष्ठति यौवनेन] 'she approaches husband through youth'

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[उप] + @deva[स्था] also takes @[ātmanepada] for: (1) @deva[देवपूजा] 'deity worship': @deva[आदित्यमुपतिष्ठते]; (2) @deva[सङ्गतिकरण] 'approaching/joining': @deva[पतिमुपतिष्ठते नारी], @deva[गङ्गायमुनामुपतिष्ठते]; (3) @deva[मित्रीकरण] 'befriending': @deva[सन्तमुपतिष्ठते साधुः]; (4) @deva[पथ] 'path leading to': @deva[अयं पन्थाः स्रुघ्नमुपतिष्ठते].}

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Optional @[ātmanepada] when meaning 'desire to obtain': @deva[भिक्षुको ब्राह्मणकुलमुपतिष्ठते] or @deva[उपतिष्ठति].}

advanced:
@deva[उप] + @deva[स्था] 'worship' → @deva[आत्मनेपद]. @deva[ऐन्द्र्या गार्हपत्यमुपतिष्ठते].

**Other meanings → parasmaipada:** @deva[भर्तारमुपतिष्ठति].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Also @[ātmanepada]: @deva[देवपूजा] (@deva[आदित्यमुपतिष्ठते]); @deva[सङ्गति] (@deva[पतिमुपतिष्ठते]); @deva[मित्री] (@deva[सन्तमुपतिष्ठते]); @deva[पथ] (@deva[पन्थाः स्रुघ्नमुपतिष्ठते]).}

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Optional with 'desire to obtain': @deva[भिक्षुको ब्राह्मणकुलमुपतिष्ठते/उपतिष्ठति].}

@deva[उप] + @deva[स्था] (intransitive 'to attend') → @deva[आत्मनेपद].

@deva[भोजनकाले उपतिष्ठते], @deva[यावदभुक्तमुपतिष्ठते].

**Transitive:** @deva[राजानमुपतिष्ठति].

@deva[अकर्मक] continues through @ref[1.3.29].

standard:
After @deva[आङ्] + @deva[यम्/हन्] used intransitively, @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies. @deva[अकर्मक] continues from @ref[1.3.26].

**Derivations:**
- @deva[आ + यम् + शप् + ते] → @deva[आयच्छते] (by @ref[7.3.77])
- @deva[आ + हन् + ते] → @deva[आहते] (by @ref[6.4.37])

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[स्वाङ्ग]-object → @deva[आत्मनेपद] even when transitive: @deva[आयच्छते पाणिम्] 'he extends his own hand.'}

After @deva[नि/सम्/उप/वि] + @deva[ह्वे], @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies even when the fruit does not accrue to the agent.

@deva[ह्वे] is marked with @deva[ञ्] in the @deva[धातुपाठ], so by @ref[1.3.72] it would take @deva[आत्मनेपद] only when the fruit accrues to the agent. This @[sūtra] extends that to all cases with these prefixes.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[अस्] 'to throw' and @deva[ऊह्] 'to note' optionally take @deva[आत्मनेपद] with @deva[उपसर्ग]s: @deva[निरस्यति/निरस्यते], @deva[समूहति/समूहते].}

After @deva[वि] + @deva[कृ] when governing a @deva[शब्द]-@deva[कर्मन्] (sound as object), @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies even when the fruit does not accrue to the agent.

**Examples:** @deva[क्रोष्टा विकुरुते स्वरान्], @deva[ध्वाङ्क्षो विकुरुते स्वरान्].

@deva[कर्मन्] here means objective case (@deva[कारक]), not 'action.' Without @deva[शब्द]-@deva[कर्मन्] → @deva[परस्मैपद]: @deva[चित्तं विकरोति].

@deva[वि] governs the next @[sūtra].

After @deva[आङ्] + @deva[क्रम्] meaning 'rising of a heavenly body,' @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies.

**Examples:** @deva[आक्रमते सूर्यः], @deva[आक्रमते चन्द्रमाः], @deva[आक्रमन्त ज्योतींषि].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{The ascending must refer to heavenly bodies. Smoke rising: @deva[आक्रामति धूमो हर्म्यतलात्] (→ @deva[परस्मैपद]).}

After @deva[सम्] + @deva[दा] with @deva[तृतीया] having the sense of @deva[चतुर्थी], @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{The instrumental has dative sense when immoral conduct is implied: @deva[दास्या संप्रयच्छते] 'he gives to entice the female servant', @deva[वृषल्या संप्रयच्छते] 'he gives to entice the prostitute.'}

Without dative sense → @deva[परस्मैपद]: @deva[पाणिना संप्रयच्छति] 'he gives with his hand.'

Note: @deva[सम्] in @ref[1.3.54] is @deva[षष्ठी] (genitive), so @deva[प्र] can intervene: @deva[संप्रयच्छते].

After desideratives of @deva[ज्ञा/श्रु/स्मृ/दृश्] (formed with @deva[सन्]), @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies.

@deva[ज्ञा] was already @deva[आत्मनेपदिन्] in certain senses (@ref[1.3.44]-@ref[1.3.46]); this @[sūtra] makes all its desideratives @deva[आत्मनेपदिन्]. Similarly, @deva[श्रु] and @deva[दृश्] with @deva[सम्] were @deva[आत्मनेपदिन्] (@ref[1.3.29] @[vārtika]); this generalizes it.

This @[sūtra] newly ordains @deva[आत्मनेपद] for @deva[स्मृ].

After @deva[प्रति/आङ्] + desiderative of @deva[श्रु], @deva[आत्मनेपद] does NOT apply. This excepts @ref[1.3.57].

**Examples:** @deva[प्रतिशुश्रूषति], @deva[आशुश्रूषति].

@deva[प्रति] and @deva[आङ्] must be @deva[उपसर्ग]s. As @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय]s: @deva[देवदत्तं प्रतिशुश्रूषते] (→ @deva[आत्मनेपद]).

After @deva[शद्] with @deva[शित्] affixes (affixes marked with indicatory @deva[श्]), @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies.

@deva[शद्] → @deva[शीय] before @deva[शित्] affixes (by @ref[7.3.78]).

**Example:** @deva[शद् + श + ते] → @deva[शीय + अ + ते] → @deva[शीयते] 'it decays.'

@deva[शित्] affixes include @deva[शप्], @deva[श], @deva[शतृ], etc. In conjugational tenses (@deva[सार्वधातुक]), @deva[शद्] is @deva[आत्मनेपदिन्]. In other tenses: @deva[शत्स्यति] (→ @deva[परस्मैपद]).

After @deva[प्र/उप] + @deva[युज्] (except with sacrificial vessels), @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies even when the fruit does not accrue to the agent.

@deva[युजिर्] is @deva[स्वरित], so by @ref[1.3.72] it's @deva[आत्मनेपदिन्] when the fruit accrues to the agent. This @[sūtra] extends that.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[आत्मनेपद] applies when preceded by any @deva[उपसर्ग] beginning or ending with a vowel—all except @deva[सम्/निर्/दुर्]: @deva[उद्युङ्क्ते], @deva[नियुङ्क्ते]. With @deva[सम्/निर्/दुर्]: @deva[संयुनक्ति] (→ @deva[परस्मैपद]).}

After @deva[स्वरितेत्] or @deva[ञित्] roots, @deva[आत्मनेपद] applies when the @deva[क्रियाफल] (fruit of action) accrues to the @deva[कर्ता].

@deva[स्वरितेत्] = root with @deva[स्वरित] accent marked on vowel (e.g., @deva[यज्]).
@deva[ञित्] = root with indicatory @deva[ञ्] (e.g., @deva[डुक्रीञ्]).

**Fruit to agent → @deva[आत्मनेपद]:** @deva[यजते] 'he sacrifices for himself', @deva[क्रीणीते] 'he buys for himself'.

**Fruit to another → @deva[परस्मैपद]:** @deva[यजति] 'he sacrifices (as priest)', @deva[क्रीणाति] 'he buys for another'.

After @deva[परि] + @deva[मृष्], @deva[परस्मैपद] applies—even when fruit accrues to agent.

@deva[मृष्] is @deva[स्वरितेत्], so @ref[1.3.72] would ordinarily apply. This @[sūtra] overrides it for @deva[परि].

**Example:** @deva[परिमृष्यति] 'he endures'.

With other @deva[उपसर्ग]s → @ref[1.3.72]: @deva[आमृष्यते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Some include @deva[परि] + @deva[वह्] here as well: @deva[परिवहति].}

After causatives of verbs not meaning @deva[निगरण] (eating/swallowing) or @deva[चलन] (moving/shaking), @deva[परस्मैपद] applies—even when fruit accrues to agent.

This applies to transitive verbs and verbs with inanimate agents.

**Non-eating/moving → @deva[परस्मैपद]:** @deva[हारयति] 'he causes to take'.

**Eating/moving → @deva[आत्मनेपद]:** @deva[निगारयते], @deva[आशयते], @deva[भोजयते], @deva[चलयते], @deva[कम्पयते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[अद्] 'to eat' takes @deva[आत्मनेपद] in causative: @deva[आदयते देवदत्तेन] 'he is made to eat by Devadatta'.}

Causatives of @deva[पा/दम्/आयम्/आयस्/परिमुह्/रुच्/नृत्/वद्/वस्] do NOT take @deva[परस्मैपद].

This is an exception to @ref[1.3.87] and @ref[1.3.88]—reinstating @deva[आत्मनेपद] per @ref[1.3.74].

@deva[पा] has sense of @deva[निगरण], @deva[नृत्] has sense of @deva[चलन], yet they still take @deva[आत्मनेपद].

**Examples:** @deva[पाययते], @deva[दमयते], @deva[आयामयते], @deva[आयासयते], @deva[परिमोहयते], @deva[रोचयते], @deva[नर्तयते], @deva[वादयते], @deva[वासयते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[धेट्] 'to suckle' should be included: @deva[धापयते शिशुम् एका समीची] 'the doe suckles the infant'.}

simple:
@deva[बहुवचन] (plural) affixes are used to denote multiplicity (more than two).

**Example:** @deva[ब्राह्मणाः पठन्ति] 'the Brahmins read'

Indeclinables (@deva[अव्यय]) have no number distinction—they always appear in @deva[एकवचन] (singular) form.

standard:
@deva[बहुवचन] (Plural) affixes express multiplicity (more than two).

**Example:** @deva[ब्राह्मणाः पठन्ति] 'the Brahmins read'

Indeclinables (@deva[अव्यय]) lack number distinction and appear only in singular.

For causatives of @deva[गति] (motion), @deva[बुद्धि] (knowledge), @deva[भक्षण] (eating), @deva[शब्दकर्म] (literary-object), and @deva[अकर्मक] (intransitive) verbs—the primitive agent becomes @deva[कर्म].

**Examples:**
- @deva[शत्रवः स्वर्गमगच्छन्] → @deva[शत्रून् स्वर्गमगमयत्]
- @deva[देवा अमृतमाश्नन्] → @deva[देवानमृतमाशयत्]
- @deva[पृथ्वी सलिले आस्त] → @deva[पृथ्वीं सलिले आसयत्]

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{Causatives of @deva[नी] and @deva[वह्] take instrumental: @deva[भृत्येन भारं नाययति].}

With @deva[हृ] and @deva[कृ] causatives, the primitive agent is optionally @deva[कर्म].

**Examples:**
- @deva[करोति कटं देवदत्तः] → @deva[कारयति कटं देवदत्तम्] or @deva[देवदत्तेन]
- @deva[हरति भारं माणवकः] → @deva[हारयति भारं माणवकम्] or @deva[माणवकेन]

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[अभिवद्] and @deva[दृश्] (@[ātmanepada]) also take optional accusative/instrumental.}

@deva[प्रादि] words with a verb = @deva[उपसर्ग].

**Examples:**
- @deva[प्रणयति] 'leads forth' (@deva[न] → @deva[ण] by @ref[8.4.14])
- @deva[प्रणायकः] 'leader'

**Contrast:** @deva[प्रनायकः] 'leaderless' (from @deva[प्रगतो नायकः])—here @deva[प्र] is with a noun, not a verb, so no @deva[उपसर्ग] status, no @deva[ण].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[मरुत्] and @deva[श्रत्] are treated as @deva[उपसर्ग]: @deva[मरुत्तः] 'given by Maruts' (@ref[7.4.47]); @deva[श्रद्धा] 'faith' (@ref[3.3.106]).}

@deva[अन्तर्] + verb = @deva[गति] when meaning @deva[अपरिग्रह] (non-acceptance, abandonment).

**Examples:**
- @deva[अन्तर्हत्य] 'having abandoned'
- @deva[अन्तर्हतम्] 'abandoned'
- @deva[यदन्तर्हन्ति] 'when he abandons'

**Contrast:** @deva[अन्तर्हत्वा मूषिकां श्येनो गतः] (@deva[अन्तर्] = 'inside')—not @deva[गति].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[अन्तर्] = @deva[उपसर्ग] for @ref[3.3.106] (@deva[अन्तर्धा]), @ref[3.3.92] (@deva[अन्तर्धिः]), @ref[8.4.14] (@deva[अन्तर्णयति]).}

@deva[साक्षात्] etc. + @deva[कृ] = optionally @deva[गति].

**Examples:**
- @deva[साक्षात्कृत्य]/@deva[साक्षात् कृत्वा]
- @deva[मिथ्याकृत्य]/@deva[मिथ्या कृत्वा]

@note[type=@[vārtika]]{@deva[साक्षात्] etc. imply @deva[च्वि] force—making evident what was concealed, or vice versa.}

@deva[मध्ये]/@deva[पदे]/@deva[निवचने] + @deva[कृ] = optionally @deva[गति] when not meaning literal placement.

**Examples:** @deva[मध्येकृत्य], @deva[पदेकृत्य], @deva[निवचनेकृत्य] (or with @deva[कृत्वा])

**Contrast:** @deva[हस्तिनः पदे कृत्वा शिरः शेते]—physical placing, no @deva[गति].

@deva[हस्ते]/@deva[पाणौ] + @deva[कृ] = obligatory @deva[गति] when meaning @deva[पाणिग्रहण] (marriage).

**Examples:** @deva[पाणौकृत्य], @deva[हस्तेकृत्य] 'having married'

**Contrast:** @deva[हस्ते कृत्वा कार्षापणं गतः]—physical taking, no @deva[गति].

@deva[जीविका]/@deva[उपनिषद्] + @deva[कृ] = @deva[गति] when meaning @deva[सादृश्य] (resemblance, 'treating as').

**Examples:** @deva[जीविकाकृत्य], @deva[उपनिषत्कृत्य]

**Contrast:** @deva[जीविकां कृत्वा गतः] (= 'having earned livelihood')—no @deva[गति].

@deva[गति] and @deva[उपसर्ग] are placed before (@deva[प्राक्]) the verb.

This establishes their nature as verbal prefixes. @deva[ते] in the @[sūtra] includes @deva[उपसर्ग] along with @deva[गति].

**Examples:** @deva[प्रगच्छति], @deva[सत्करोति], @deva[अलंकरोति], etc.

@deva[अनु] is @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] when meaning @deva[हीन] 'inferior to.'

**Example:** @deva[अनुशाकटायनं वैयाकरणाः] 'grammarians are inferior to @[śākaṭāyana]'

The word @deva[हीन] is comparative—it requires the superior term for comparison. @deva[अनु] governs this superior term in the accusative.

@deva[अभि] is @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] for @deva[लक्षण], circumstance, and @deva[ईप्सा]—but not for @deva[भाग] (share).

**Examples:** @deva[वृक्षमभि विद्योतते] (direction); @deva[मातरमभि साधुः] (circumstance).

**Contrast:** @deva[यदत्र ममाभिष्यात्]—for 'share,' @deva[अभि] is @deva[उपसर्ग], causing @deva[स] → @deva[ष].

@deva[अधि] and @deva[परि] are @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] when functioning as expletives (surplusage).

**Examples:** @deva[कुतोऽभ्यागच्छति] = @deva[कुतः पर्यागच्छति] 'whence has he come?'

Calling them @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] prevents them from being classified as @deva[उपसर्ग] or @deva[गति], which would trigger their associated rules.

@deva[अधि] is optionally @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय] when followed by @deva[कृ].

**Example:** @deva[यदत्र मामधि करिष्यति] 'what he will do regarding me'

If @deva[गति]: accent follows @ref[8.1.71]. If @deva[कर्मप्रवचनीय]: different accent pattern.

@deva[संहिता] = @deva[परः सन्निकर्षः] 'utmost proximity'—the closest possible contact between sounds.

**Example:** @deva[दधि] + @deva[अत्र] → @deva[दध्यत्र] (sandhi applies because they're in @deva[संहिता])

Without @deva[संहिता], words are pronounced separately and no euphonic changes occur. The sixth @deva[अध्याय] largely deals with @deva[संहिता] operations.

advanced:
@deva[अप], @deva[परि], @deva[बहिस्], @deva[अञ्च्वन्त] + @deva[पञ्चम्यन्त] → @deva[विभाषा] @deva[अव्ययीभाव].

- @deva[अपत्रिगर्तम्] / @deva[अप त्रिगर्तेभ्यः]
- @deva[परित्रिगर्तम्] / @deva[परि त्रिगर्तेभ्यः]
- @deva[बहिर्ग्रामम्] / @deva[बहिर् ग्रामात्]
- @deva[प्राग्ग्रामम्] / @deva[प्राक् ग्रामात्]

@deva[अञ्चु]-forms: @deva[उदञ्च्], @deva[प्राञ्च्], etc.

@deva[ज्ञापक]: @deva[बहिस्] governs @deva[पञ्चमी] (@ref[2.3.29]).

standard:
@deva[आङ्] (@deva[मर्यादा] / @deva[अभिविधि]) + @deva[पञ्चम्यन्त] → optional @deva[अव्ययीभाव].

- @deva[मर्यादा] (exclusive): @deva[आपाटलिपुत्रं वृष्टो देवः] 'it rained up to (but not including) @[pāṭaliputra]'
- @deva[अभिविधि] (inclusive): @deva[आकुमारं यशः पाणिनेः] '@[pāṇini]'s fame extends even to the boys'

advanced:
@deva[आङ्] (@deva[मर्यादायाम्] / @deva[अभिविधौ]) + @deva[पञ्चम्यन्त] → @deva[विभाषा] @deva[अव्ययीभाव].

- @deva[मर्यादा]: @deva[आपाटलिपुत्रं वृष्टो देवः] / @deva[आ पाटलिपुत्रात्]
- @deva[अभिविधि]: @deva[आकुमारं यशः पाणिनेः] / @deva[आ कुमारेभ्यः]

@deva[सङ्ख्या] + @deva[वंश्य] → @deva[विभाषा] @deva[अव्ययीभाव].

@deva[वंश] = descent through birth or knowledge. @deva[द्विमुनि व्याकरणस्य] (@[pāṇini], @[patañjali]), @deva[त्रिमुनि व्याकरणस्य] (+ @[kātyāyana]).

Equality: @deva[द्विमुनि व्याकरणम्]. Birth: @deva[एकविंशति भारद्वाजम्].

These are @deva[द्विगु]-like.

standard:
@deva[सुबन्त] + river name → @deva[नित्य] @deva[अव्ययीभाव] when the compound is a @deva[संज्ञा] denoting something other than its parts.

@deva[सङ्ख्या] @deva[अनुवृत्ति] doesn't extend here. Though in the @deva[विभाषा] section, this is @deva[नित्य]—@deva[संज्ञा]s cannot be expressed by sentences.

Examples: @deva[उन्मत्तगङ्गम्], @deva[लोहितगङ्गम्], @deva[कृष्णगङ्गम्], @deva[शनैर्गङ्गम्].

No compound when not @deva[अन्यपदार्थ]: @deva[कृष्णवेणा] 'the river @[kṛṣṇaveṇā].'
No compound when not @deva[संज्ञा]: @deva[शीघ्रो गङ्गो देशः].

advanced:
@deva[सुबन्त] + @deva[नदी] → @deva[नित्य] @deva[अव्ययीभाव] when @deva[अन्यपदार्थ] and @deva[संज्ञा].

@deva[सङ्ख्या] @deva[अनुवृत्ति] stops. @deva[नित्य] because @deva[संज्ञा] cannot be expressed by @deva[वाक्य].

Examples: @deva[उन्मत्तगङ्गम्], @deva[लोहितगङ्गम्], @deva[कृष्णगङ्गम्], @deva[शनैर्गङ्गम्].

No compound: @deva[कृष्णवेणा] (not @deva[अन्यपदार्थ]), @deva[शीघ्रो गङ्गो देशः] (not @deva[संज्ञा]).

@deva[तत्पुरुष] @deva[अधिकार] through @ref[2.2.23]. @deva[उत्तरपदार्थप्रधान] @deva[समास].

@deva[कर्मधारय], @deva[द्विगु] are @deva[तत्पुरुष] sub-types. The term predates @[pāṇini].

This @deva[पाद] + 22 @deva[सूत्र]s of next @deva[पाद] treat @deva[तत्पुरुष].

standard:
@deva[खट्वा] (@deva[द्वितीया]) + @deva[क्तान्त] (@deva[क्षेपे]) → @deva[तत्पुरुष].

@deva[क्षेप] = censure/blame. The reproachful sense belongs to the whole compound, not its parts—hence @deva[नित्य] @deva[समास] (cannot be analyzed back).

Examples: @deva[खट्वारूढः], @deva[खट्वाप्लुतः] = 'fool, someone who went astray.'

No compound without @deva[क्षेप]: @deva[खट्वाम् आरूढः] 'lying on a bed.'

Background: @deva[ब्रह्मचारी]s must sleep on ground. @deva[खट्वारूढः] originally = 'one who prematurely took to married life'—later generalized.

advanced:
@deva[खट्वा] (@deva[द्वितीयान्त]) + @deva[क्तान्त] (@deva[क्षेपे]) → @deva[नित्य] @deva[तत्पुरुष].

@deva[क्षेप] sense in compound only—@deva[नित्य] because unanalyzable. @deva[खट्वारूढः], @deva[खट्वाप्लुतः] = fool.

No compound without @deva[क्षेप]: @deva[खट्वाम् आरूढः].

Etymology: @deva[ब्रह्मचारी]s sleep on ground. @deva[खट्वारूढः] = premature householder → fool.

standard:
@deva[तृतीयान्त] (@deva[मिश्रीकरण]) + @deva[भक्ष्यवाचक] → @deva[तत्पुरुष].

@deva[भक्ष्य] = anything edible (hard or soft); @deva[मिश्रीकरण] = ingredient that refines or flavors it.

**Examples:**
- @deva[गुडधानाः] 'barley prepared with jaggery'
- @deva[गुडपृथकाः] 'flattened parched rice with jaggery'

As with @ref[2.1.34], an understood verb connects the two words.

advanced:
@deva[तृतीयान्त] (@deva[मिश्रीकरणवाचक]) + @deva[भक्ष्यवाचक] → @deva[तत्पुरुष].

@deva[भक्ष्य] = any edible; @deva[मिश्रीकरण] = flavoring/refining ingredient.

**Examples:** @deva[गुडधानाः], @deva[गुडपृथकाः].

As in @ref[2.1.34], an understood verb establishes the semantic connection.

standard:
A @deva[षष्ठी]-ending word compounds with @deva[याजक] etc. This overrides @ref[2.2.16], which would block genitive compounds with @deva[कर्तृ]-denoting @deva[अक]-words.

**Examples:** @deva[ब्राह्मणयाजकः], @deva[क्षत्रिययाजकः].

**The @deva[याजकादि] list:** @deva[याजक], @deva[पूजक], @deva[परिचारक], @deva[परिवेषक], @deva[परिषेचक], @deva[स्नापक]/@deva[स्नातक], @deva[अध्यापक], @deva[उत्साहक]/@deva[उत्सादक], @deva[उद्वर्तक], @deva[होतृ], @deva[नर्तृ], @deva[रथगणक], @deva[पत्तिगणक], @deva[पोतृ], @deva[हर्तृ], @deva[वर्तक].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: A genitive compounds with a word expressing a quality that inheres in the genitive referent: @deva[ब्राह्मणवर्णः] '@deva[ब्राह्मण]-caste', @deva[चन्दनगन्धः] 'sandal-scent'.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Also with comparatives—the @deva[तर] is elided: @deva[सर्वेषां श्वेततरः] → @deva[सर्वश्वेतः] 'whitest of all'.

advanced:
@deva[षष्ठी]-ending words compound with @deva[याजकादि] words. This overrides @ref[2.2.16].

**Examples:** @deva[ब्राह्मणयाजकः], @deva[क्षत्रिययाजकः].

**@deva[याजकादि]:** @deva[याजक], @deva[पूजक], @deva[परिचारक], @deva[परिवेषक], @deva[परिषेचक], @deva[स्नापक], @deva[अध्यापक], @deva[उत्साहक], @deva[उद्वर्तक], @deva[होतृ], @deva[नर्तृ], @deva[रथगणक], @deva[पत्तिगणक], @deva[पोतृ], @deva[हर्तृ], @deva[वर्तक].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Genitive compounds with @deva[गुण] inhering in referent: @deva[ब्राह्मणवर्णः], @deva[चन्दनगन्धः], @deva[कपित्थरसः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: With comparatives (@deva[तर] elided): @deva[सर्वश्वेतः], @deva[सर्वमहान्]—exception to @ref[2.2.10].

@deva[तृतीयादि]-@deva[उपपद] optionally compounds with @deva[क्त्वान्त]. When compounded, @deva[क्त्वा] → @deva[ल्यप्] (@ref[7.1.37]).

**Example:** @deva[उच्चैःकृत्य] ~ @deva[उच्चैः कृत्वा].

**@deva[तृतीयादि] required:** @deva[अलं कृत्वा], @deva[खलु कृत्वा]—no compound.

@deva[दिङ्नामानि] compound when @deva[अन्तरालार्थ]. @deva[बहुव्रीहि].

**Examples:** @deva[दक्षिणपूर्वा], @deva[पूर्वोत्तरा].

**@deva[नाम] restriction:** Derivatives not @deva[दिक्] as primary sense don't compound: @deva[ऐन्द्र्याश्च कौबेर्याश्च दिशोर्यदन्तरालम्].

standard:
The @deva[उपसर्जन] (@ref[1.2.43])—the word exhibited in nominative in the compounding rules—is placed first (@deva[पूर्वनिपात]).

**Example:** @deva[राजपुरुषः].

@deva[समासे] is understood.

advanced:
The @deva[कर्तृ] (@ref[1.4.54]: @deva[स्वतन्त्रः कर्ता]) or @deva[करण] (@ref[1.4.42]: @deva[साधकतमं करणम्]) takes @deva[तृतीया].

**Examples:** @deva[देवदत्तेन कृतम्], @deva[दात्रेण लुनाति], @deva[यज्ञदत्तेन भुक्तम्], @deva[परशुना छिनत्ति].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Additional words taking @deva[तृतीया]: @deva[प्रकृति], @deva[प्राय], @deva[गोत्र], @deva[सम], @deva[विषम], @deva[द्विद्रोण], @deva[पञ्चक], @deva[साहस्र]. Examples: @deva[प्रायेण याज्ञिकः], @deva[गार्ग्योऽस्मि गोत्रेण], @deva[समेन विषमेण वा धावति], @deva[द्विद्रोणेन क्रीणाति].

With @deva[सर्वनामन्] + @deva[हेतु], both @deva[षष्ठी] and @deva[तृतीया] apply.

**Examples:** @deva[कस्य/केन हेतुना वसति], @deva[यस्य/येन हेतुना वसति].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: With @deva[निमित्त], @deva[कारण], or @deva[प्रयोजन], nearly all @deva[विभक्ति]s are possible: @deva[किं निमित्तम्], @deva[केन निमित्तेन], @deva[कस्मै निमित्ताय], @deva[कस्मान्निमित्तात्], @deva[कस्मिन् निमित्ते वसति].

standard:
The @deva[अपादान कारक] (source of separation, per @ref[1.4.24]: @deva[ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम्]) takes @deva[पञ्चमी].

**Examples:**
- @deva[ग्रामादागच्छति] 'he comes from the village'
- @deva[वृकेभ्यो बिभेति] 'he fears wolves'
- @deva[अध्ययनात् पराजयते] 'he is defeated in study'

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: When a @deva[ल्यप्]-ending participle is elided, @deva[पञ्चमी] marks the location: @deva[प्रासादमारुह्य प्रेक्षते] = @deva[प्रासादात् प्रेक्षते] 'he sees from a palace'.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: In questions/answers about origin: @deva[कुतो भवान्? पाटलिपुत्रात्] 'Whence are you? From @[pāṭaliputra].'

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: For measuring distance in space/time: @deva[गवीधूमतः साङ्काश्यं चत्वारि योजनानि] '@[sāṅkāśya] is four yojanas from @[gavīdhūma]'; @deva[कार्त्तिक्या आग्रहायणी मासे] '@[āgrahāyaṇī] is one month from @[kārttikā]'.

advanced:
The @deva[अपादान] (@ref[1.4.24]: @deva[ध्रुवमपायेऽपादानम्]) takes @deva[पञ्चमी].

**Examples:** @deva[ग्रामादागच्छति], @deva[वृकेभ्यो बिभेति] (@ref[1.4.25]), @deva[अध्ययनात् पराजयते] (@ref[1.4.26]).

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[ल्यप्]-elision → @deva[पञ्चमी] for location: @deva[प्रासादात् प्रेक्षते], @deva[आसनात् प्रेक्षते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Distance measurement: @deva[गवीधूमतः साङ्काश्यं चत्वारि योजनानि] (space in nom. or loc.); @deva[कार्त्तिक्या आग्रहायणी मासे] (time in loc.).

With @deva[अन्यार्थ] ('other'), @deva[आरात्], @deva[इतर], @deva[ऋते], @deva[दिक्शब्द]s, @deva[अञ्चु]-compounds, or @deva[आच्]/@deva[आहि]-endings, @deva[पञ्चमी] applies.

**Examples:** @deva[अन्यो देवदत्तात्], @deva[आराद् देवदत्तात्], @deva[ऋते देवदत्तात्], @deva[पूर्वो ग्रामात्], @deva[प्राक् ग्रामात्], @deva[दक्षिणाहि ग्रामात्].

@deva[अञ्चु]-words (@deva[प्राक्], @deva[प्रत्यक्]) are also @deva[दिक्शब्द]s; their explicit mention excludes @ref[2.3.30]'s @deva[षष्ठी].

@deva[दूर] and @deva[अन्तिक] themselves take @deva[द्वितीया], @deva[पञ्चमी], or @deva[तृतीया].

**Examples:** @deva[दूरं/दूराद्/दूरेण ग्रामस्य], @deva[अन्तिकं/अन्तिकात्/अन्तिकेन ग्रामस्य].

Restriction: When used as substantives (not meaning distance): @deva[दूरः पन्थाः], @deva[दूराय पथे देहि]—regular declension applies.

standard:
The @deva[अधिकरण कारक] (location, per @ref[1.4.45]: @deva[आधारोऽधिकरणम्]) takes @deva[सप्तमी]. Also, words meaning @deva[दूर] 'distant' and @deva[अन्तिक] 'near' take @deva[सप्तमी].

**Examples:**
- @deva[कटे आस्ते] 'he sits on the mat'
- @deva[स्थाल्यां पचति] 'he cooks in the pot'
- @deva[अन्तिके/दूरे ग्रामस्य] 'near/far from the village'

Thus @deva[दूर] and @deva[अन्तिक] take four cases: @deva[द्वितीया], @deva[तृतीया], @deva[पञ्चमी], @deva[सप्तमी].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Words like @deva[अधीतिन्] 'learned' (@deva[क्त] + @deva[इनि]) govern locative: @deva[अधीती व्याकरणे] 'versed in grammar'.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[साधु/असाधु] govern locative of the person toward whom: @deva[मातरि साधुः] 'good toward mother'.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Locative for purpose: @deva[चर्मणि द्वीपिनं हन्ति] 'he kills the tiger for its skin'.

advanced:
The @deva[अधिकरण] (@ref[1.4.45]) takes @deva[सप्तमी]. Also @deva[दूर/अन्तिक]-meaning words take @deva[सप्तमी].

**Examples:** @deva[कटे आस्ते], @deva[स्थाल्यां पचति], @deva[अन्तिके/दूरे ग्रामस्य].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[क्त] + @deva[इनि] words govern locative: @deva[अधीती व्याकरणे] (@ref[5.2.88]).

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[साधु/असाधु] + locative: @deva[मातरि साधुः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Locative absolute for simultaneous (non-temporal) actions: @deva[ऋद्धेषु भुञ्जानेषु दरिद्रा आसते].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Locative for purpose: @deva[चर्मणि द्वीपिनं हन्ति], @deva[दन्तयोर्हन्ति कुञ्जरम्].

In @deva[निर्धारण] (specification), both @deva[षष्ठी] and @deva[सप्तमी] apply to the group from which the individual is singled out.

**Examples:** @deva[गवां/गोषु कृष्णा बहुक्षीरा], @deva[मनुष्याणां/मनुष्येषु क्षत्रियः शूरतमः].

@deva[निर्धारण] = separating one from many by @deva[जाति], @deva[गुण], or @deva[क्रिया] (@ref[2.2.10]).

@deva[प्रथमा] applies when the sense is @deva[प्रातिपदिकार्थ], @deva[लिङ्ग], @deva[परिमाण], or @deva[संख्या].

**Examples:** @deva[वृक्षः] (stem-meaning), @deva[कुमारी] (gender), @deva[द्रोणः/खारी/आढकः] (measure), @deva[एकः/द्वौ/बहवः] (number).

@deva[प्रातिपदिक] = @deva[अर्थवदधातुरप्रत्ययः प्रातिपदिकम्] (@ref[1.2.45]). @deva[निपात]-s which denote nothing are also @deva[प्रातिपदिक].

@deva[प्रथमा] also applies when the sense is @deva[सम्बोधन] (addressing).

**Examples:** @deva[हे राम], @deva[हे रामौ], @deva[हे रामाः].

This extends @deva[प्रथमा] beyond @ref[2.3.46] to include vocative sense.

@deva[षष्ठी] applies in @deva[शेष]—relations other than @deva[कारक] (verb-related) and @deva[प्रातिपदिकार्थ].

**Examples:** @deva[राज्ञः पुरुषः] (ownership), @deva[पशोः पादः] (part-whole), @deva[पितुः पुत्रः] (kinship).

@deva[शेष] = residual relations (@deva[स्वस्वामिभाव], @deva[अवयवावयविभाव], @deva[जन्य]-@deva[जनकभाव], etc.).

In @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[षष्ठी] diversely replaces @deva[तृतीया] for @deva[करण] of @deva[यज्].

**Examples:** @deva[घृतस्य/घृतेन यजते], @deva[सोमस्य/सोमेन यजते].

@deva[बहुलम्] = optional/irregular.

When both @deva[कर्तृ] and @deva[कर्मन्] are expressed with @deva[कृत्]-word, @deva[कर्मन्] → @deva[षष्ठी], @deva[कर्तृ] → @deva[तृतीया].

**Examples:** @deva[गवां दोहोऽगोपालकेन], @deva[ओदनस्य भोजनं देवदत्तेन].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[कर्तृ] optionally takes @deva[षष्ठी/तृतीया] with feminine @deva[कृत्]: @deva[जगतः कृतिर्हरेः/हरिणा], @deva[सूत्रस्य कृतिः पाणिनेः/पाणिनिना].

@deva[क्त] in @deva[अधिकरण] sense (@ref[3.4.76]) takes @deva[षष्ठी].

**Examples:** @deva[इदमेषामासितम्], @deva[इदमेषां शयितम्].

Exception to @ref[2.3.69].

@deva[द्विकर्मक] verbs: both @deva[कर्मन्] → @deva[षष्ठी]: @deva[नेताऽश्वस्य ग्रामस्य चैत्रः]. If one principal: @deva[नेताऽश्वस्य ग्रामं चैत्रः].

@deva[षष्ठी] prohibited for @deva[कर्तृ/कर्मन्] with @deva[लोक] (@deva[ल]+@deva[उ]+@deva[उक]), @deva[कृत्]-@deva[अव्यय], @deva[निष्ठा], @deva[खलर्थ], @deva[तृन्]. This debars @ref[2.3.65].

@deva[कर्तृ] → @deva[तृतीया], @deva[कर्मन्] → @deva[द्वितीया].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] Exception: @deva[तोसुन्/कसुन्] (@ref[3.4.16-17]) allow @deva[षष्ठी]: @deva[पुरा सूर्यस्योदेतोः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[कामुक] in @deva[भाषा] takes @deva[षष्ठी]: @deva[दास्याः कामुकः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[द्विष्] + @deva[शतृ] optional: @deva[चौरं/चौरस्य द्विषन्].

@deva[षष्ठी] prohibited with @deva[अक] (@deva[भविष्यत्]) or @deva[इन्] (@deva[भविष्यत्/ऋण]).

**Examples:** @deva[कटं कारको व्रजति], @deva[ग्रामं गमी], @deva[शतं दायी].

**Counterexamples:** @deva[यवानां लावकः], @deva[वर्षशतस्य पूरकः]—different @deva[अक] (@ref[3.1.133], not @deva[भविष्यत्]-@deva[अक]).

With @deva[कृत्य] (@ref[3.1.95]), @deva[कर्तृ] optionally takes @deva[षष्ठी]; @deva[कर्मन्] obligatorily does (by @ref[2.3.65]).

**Examples:** @deva[भवतः/भवता कटः कर्तव्यः], @deva[गेयो माणवकः साम्नाम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[द्विकर्मक] verbs: @deva[षष्ठी] prohibited: @deva[क्रष्टव्या ग्रामं शाखा देवदत्तेन], @deva[नेतव्या ग्रामम् अजा देवदत्तेन].

With @deva[सादृश्य]-meaning words, @deva[तृतीया/षष्ठी] optional—except @deva[तुला/उपमा] (only @deva[षष्ठी]).

**Examples:** @deva[तुल्यो/सदृशो देवदत्तेन/देवदत्तस्य]. With @deva[तुला/उपमा]: @deva[तुला देवदत्तस्य नास्ति], @deva[उपमा कृष्णस्य न विद्यते].

@deva[अन्यतरस्याम्] repeated for @deva[अनुवृत्ति] into @ref[2.3.73].

@deva[द्विगु] expresses @deva[एकवचन] sense (@deva[समाहार]).

**Examples:** @deva[पञ्चगवम्], @deva[पञ्चपूली] (@ref[4.1.21]).

Applies to @deva[समाहार-द्विगु] (collective). Singular persists with further affixes: @deva[पञ्चपूलीयं शोभना].

@deva[समाहार-द्वन्द्व] of body parts, musicians, or soldiers takes @deva[एकवचन] @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग].

**Examples:** @deva[पाणिपादम्], @deva[शिरोग्रीवम्], @deva[मार्दङ्गिकपाणविकम्], @deva[रथिकाश्वारोहम्], @deva[वीणावादकपरिवादकम्], @deva[रथिकपादातम्].

Applies only to @deva[समाहार-द्वन्द्व], not @deva[इतरेतर-द्वन्द्व] (@ref[2.2.29]). Compounds like @deva[दधिपयसी] (@ref[2.4.14]) are purely @deva[इतरेतर]; compounds of trees/animals (@ref[2.4.12]) are optionally either.

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[अध्वर्यु]-@deva[क्रतु] (Yajurveda sacrifices) takes @deva[एकवचन] if not @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग].

**Examples:** @deva[अर्काश्वमेधम्], @deva[सायाह्नातिरात्रम्].

Not Yajurveda: @deva[इषुवज्रौ], @deva[उद्भिद्वलभिदौ]. Neuter words: @deva[राजसूयवाजपेयौ]. @deva[दर्शपौर्णमासौ] excluded—@deva[क्रतु] technically means @deva[सोम]-sacrifices only.

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of words denoting students of sequentially-related subjects (@deva[अदूरविद्य]) takes @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[पदकक्रमकम्], @deva[क्रमकवार्त्तिकम्].

Not study-order: @deva[पितापुत्रौ]. Remote subjects: @deva[याज्ञिकवैयाकरणौ].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[द्रव्यजाति] (genus of substances), not living beings, takes @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[आराशस्त्रि], @deva[धानाशष्कुलि].

Living: @deva[ब्राह्मणक्षत्रियौ]. Proper names: @deva[नन्दकपाञ्चजन्यौ]. @deva[गुणजाति]: @deva[रूपरसगन्धस्पर्शाः]. @deva[क्रियाजाति]: @deva[गमनाकुञ्चनप्रसारणानि]. Individuals: @deva[इह कुण्डे बदरामलकानि तिष्ठन्ति].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of different-gender river/country names (not @deva[ग्राम]) takes @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[गङ्गाशोणम्], @deva[कुरुकुरुक्षेत्रम्].

Same gender: @deva[गङ्गायमुने], @deva[मद्रकेकयाः]. Towns: @deva[जाम्बवशालूकिन्यौ]. Mountains excluded: @deva[कैलासगन्धमादने].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[नगर] allowed: @deva[मथुरापाटलिपुत्रम्]. @deva[ग्राम]+@deva[नगर]: @deva[सौर्यकेतवते].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[क्षुद्रजन्तु] takes @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[यूकालिक्षम्], @deva[दंशमशकम्].

@deva[क्षुद्रजन्तु] defined variously: invertebrates, very small animals, or all below mongoose.

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[शाश्वतिकविरोध] (permanent enmity) animals takes @deva[एकवचन] invariably.

**Examples:** @deva[मार्जारमूषकम्], @deva[अहिनकुलम्], @deva[काकोलूकम्], @deva[श्वशृगालम्], @deva[अश्वमहिषम्].

Temporary quarrel: @deva[गौपालिशालङ्कायनाः कलहायन्ते]. @deva[च] = @deva[एव]—invariable, overrides @ref[2.4.12].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[अनिर्वासित शूद्र] takes @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[तक्षायस्करम्], @deva[रजकतन्तुवायम्].

@deva[अनिर्वासित] = can share food vessels without permanent defilement. Expelled: @deva[चण्डालमृतपाः].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of trees, wild animals, grass, grain, condiments, domestic beasts/birds, @deva[अश्ववडव], @deva[पूर्वापर], @deva[अधरोत्तर]—optionally @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[प्लक्षन्यग्रोधम्]/‍@deva[°ाः], @deva[रुरुपृषतम्]/‍@deva[°ाः], @deva[कुशकाशम्]/‍@deva[°ाः], @deva[व्रीहियवम्]/‍@deva[°ाः], @deva[दधिघृतम्]/‍@deva[°ते], @deva[गोमहिषम्]/‍@deva[°षाः], @deva[तित्तिरकपिञ्जलम्]/‍@deva[°लाः], @deva[अश्ववडवम्]/‍@deva[°वाः], @deva[पूर्वापरम्]/‍@deva[°रे], @deva[अधरोत्तरम्]/‍@deva[°रे].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] Singular for large quantity; dual for individuals: @deva[प्लक्षन्यग्रोधौ], @deva[रुरुपृषतौ], @deva[हंसचक्रवाकौ], @deva[व्रीहियवौ], @deva[कुशकाशौ].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] of @deva[विप्रतिषिद्ध] (contraries), not substances, optionally @deva[एकवचन]. @deva[च] continues @deva[विभाषा] from previous @[sūtra].

**Examples:** @deva[शीतोष्णम्]/‍@deva[°ष्णे], @deva[सुखदुःखम्]/‍@deva[°खे], @deva[जीवितमरणम्]/‍@deva[°णे].

Not contrary: @deva[कामक्रोधौ]. Substances: @deva[शीतोष्णे उदके].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] with @deva[संख्येय] (fixed number) of @deva[अधिकरण] (concrete things) doesn't take @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[दश दन्तोष्ठाः], @deva[दश मार्दङ्गिकपाणविकाः].

Compare @ref[2.4.2].

@deva[द्वन्द्व] with approximate number optionally @deva[एकवचन].

**Examples:** @deva[उपदशं दन्तोष्ठम्]/‍@deva[उपदशा दन्तोष्ठाः], @deva[उपदशं मार्दङ्गिकपाणविकम्]/‍@deva[उपदशा मार्दङ्गिकपाणविकाः].

Singular = @deva[अव्ययीभाव]; proper number = @deva[बहुव्रीहि] (@ref[2.2.25]).

standard:
@deva[द्विगु] and @deva[द्वन्द्व] compounds ordained @deva[एकवचन] by previous rules are @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग].

**Examples:** @deva[दशगवम्], @deva[पाणिपादम्], @deva[शिरोग्रीवम्].

This debars @ref[2.4.26] (gender of final member).

@note[type=@[vārtika]] Short-@deva[अ] ending @deva[द्विगु] = feminine: @deva[पञ्चपूली], @deva[दशरथी].
@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[आप्]-ending optionally feminine: @deva[पञ्चखट्वम्]/‍@deva[पञ्चखट्वी].
@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[अन्]-ending optionally feminine (@deva[न्] elided): @deva[पञ्चतक्षम्]/‍@deva[पञ्चतक्षी].
@note[type=@[vārtika]] Exception: @deva[पात्र]-class remains neuter: @deva[पञ्चपात्रम्], @deva[चतुर्युगम्], @deva[त्रिभुवनम्].

advanced:
@deva[द्विगु]/@deva[द्वन्द्व] with @deva[एकवचन] = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग]. Debars @ref[2.4.26].

**Examples:** @deva[दशगवम्], @deva[पाणिपादम्], @deva[शिरोग्रीवम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] Short-@deva[अ] @deva[द्विगु] = fem: @deva[पञ्चपूली]. @deva[आप्]-ending optional: @deva[पञ्चखट्वम्]/‍@deva[°ी]. @deva[अन्]-ending optional (@deva[न्] elided): @deva[पञ्चतक्षम्]/‍@deva[°ी]. @deva[पात्र]-class neuter: @deva[पञ्चपात्रम्], @deva[चतुर्युगम्], @deva[त्रिभुवनम्].

standard:
An @deva[अव्ययीभाव] compound (@ref[2.1.6]) is @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग].

**Examples:** @deva[अधिस्त्रि] 'pertaining to a woman', @deva[उपकुमारि], @deva[उन्मत्तगङ्गम्].

Without this rule, @deva[अव्ययीभाव] would lack gender (first member is indeclinable) or follow final member.

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[पुण्य]/‍@deva[सुदिन] + @deva[अहन्] = neuter: @deva[पुण्याहम्], @deva[सुदिनाहम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[पथ] with numeral/avyaya = neuter: @deva[त्रिपथम्], @deva[चतुष्पथम्], @deva[विपथम्], @deva[सुपथम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]] Adverbs qualifying verbs = neuter accusative: @deva[मृदु पचति], @deva[शोभनं पचति].

advanced:
@deva[अव्ययीभाव] (@ref[2.1.6]) = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग]. @deva[च] includes additional cases.

**Examples:** @deva[अधिस्त्रि], @deva[उपकुमारि], @deva[उन्मत्तगङ्गम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[पुण्य]/‍@deva[सुदिन] + @deva[अहन्]: @deva[पुण्याहम्], @deva[सुदिनाहम्]. @deva[पथ] + numeral/avyaya: @deva[त्रिपथम्], @deva[चतुष्पथम्], @deva[विपथम्], @deva[सुपथम्]. Adverbs: @deva[मृदु पचति], @deva[शोभनं पचति].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] (excluding @deva[नञ्]/@deva[कर्मधारय]) = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] in following @[sūtras]. @deva[अधिकार].

**Example:** @deva[ब्राह्मणसेनम्]/‍@deva[°ना] (@ref[2.4.25]).

Excluded: @deva[असेना] (@deva[नञ्]), @deva[परमसेना] (@deva[कर्मधारय]), @deva[दृढसेनो राजा] (not @deva[तत्पुरुष]).

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[कन्था] = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] when appellative in @deva[उशीनर] country.

**Examples:** @deva[सौशमिकन्थम्], @deva[आह्वरकन्थम्].

Not appellative: @deva[वीरणकन्था]. Not @[uśīnara]: @deva[दाक्षिकन्था]. Debars @ref[2.4.26]. Accent: @ref[4.2.124].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[उपज्ञा]/@deva[उपक्रम] = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] for origin of works.

**Examples:** @deva[पाणिन्युपज्ञमाकालापकं व्याकरणम्], @deva[व्याड्युपज्ञं दुष्करणम्], @deva[आढ्योपक्रमः प्रासादः], @deva[नन्दोपक्रमाणि मानानि].

Not origin: @deva[देवदत्तोपज्ञो रथः], @deva[यज्ञदत्तोपक्रमो रथः]. Without @deva[उपज्ञा]: @deva[वाल्मीकिश्लोकाः]. Accent: @ref[6.2.14].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[छाया] = invariable @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] for profusion.

**Examples:** @deva[शलभच्छायम्], @deva[इक्षुच्छायम्].

Not profusion: @deva[कुड्यच्छाया]. @ref[2.4.25] optional; this invariable. Accent: @ref[6.2.14].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[सभा] = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] after @deva[राजन्]-synonyms or @deva[अमनुष्य].

**Examples:** @deva[इन्द्रसभम्], @deva[ईश्वरसभम्], @deva[रक्षःसभम्], @deva[पिशाचसभम्].

@deva[राजसभा] excluded (only synonyms; exception to @ref[1.1.68]). Human: @deva[देवदत्तसभा], @deva[काष्ठसभा].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[सभा] = @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] for concourse (not building).

**Examples:** @deva[स्त्रीसभम्], @deva[दासीसभम्].

Building: @deva[अनाथसभा].

@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[सेना]/@deva[सुरा]/@deva[छाया]/@deva[शाला]/@deva[निशा] = optional @deva[नपुंसकलिङ्ग] (not @deva[नञ्]/@deva[कर्मधारय]).

**Examples:** @deva[ब्राह्मणसेना]/‍@deva[°म्], @deva[यवसुरा]/‍@deva[°म्], @deva[कुड्यच्छाया]/‍@deva[°म्], @deva[गोशाला]/‍@deva[°म्], @deva[श्वनिशा]/‍@deva[°म्].

Excluded: @deva[असेना] (@deva[नञ्]), @deva[परमसेना] (@deva[कर्मधारय]). Accent: @ref[6.2.14], @ref[6.2.123].

@deva[द्वन्द्व]/@deva[तत्पुरुष] = gender of final member. Applies to @deva[इतरेतर-द्वन्द्व]; @deva[समाहार] = neuter.

**Examples:** @deva[कुक्कुटमयूर्यौ इमे] (fem.), @deva[मयूरीकुक्कुटौ इमौ] (masc.), @deva[अर्धपिप्पली], @deva[अर्धकोशातकी].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] Exceptions: @deva[द्विगु], @deva[प्राप्त]/@deva[आपन्न]/@deva[अलम्] compounds, @deva[गति] compounds: @deva[पञ्चकपालः], @deva[प्राप्तजीविकः], @deva[निष्कौशाम्बिः].

@deva[अश्ववडव] = gender of first member. Exception to @ref[2.4.26].

**Example:** @deva[अश्ववडवौ इमौ], @deva[अश्ववडवान्], @deva[अश्ववडवैः] (all masc.).

Not @deva[समाहार]; if @deva[समाहार] (@ref[2.4.12]), neuter: @deva[अश्ववडवम्].

standard:
@deva[द्वन्द्व] and @deva[तत्पुरुष] ending in @deva[रात्र] or @deva[अह्न] are @deva[पुंलिङ्ग].

**Examples:**
- @deva[द्विरात्रः], @deva[त्रिरात्रः] 'two/three nights'
- @deva[पूर्वाह्णः], @deva[अपराह्णः], @deva[मध्याह्नः] 'forenoon, afternoon, noon'
- @deva[द्व्यहः], @deva[त्र्यहः] 'two/three days'

@deva[रात्र] formed by @deva[रात्रि] + @deva[अच्] (@ref[5.4.87]); @deva[अह्न] by @ref[5.4.88]; @deva[अह] by @ref[5.4.91]. Debars @ref[2.4.26].

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[अनुवाक]-class masculine: @deva[अनुवाकः], @deva[शंयुवाकः], @deva[सूक्तवाकः].

advanced:
@deva[द्वन्द्व]/@deva[तत्पुरुष] + @deva[रात्र]/@deva[अह्न] = @deva[पुंलिङ्ग]. Debars @ref[2.4.26].

**Examples:** @deva[द्विरात्रः], @deva[त्रिरात्रः], @deva[पूर्वाह्णः], @deva[अपराह्णः], @deva[मध्याह्नः], @deva[द्व्यहः], @deva[त्र्यहः].

@deva[रात्र] = @deva[रात्रि] + @deva[अच्] (@ref[5.4.87]); @deva[अह्न] (@ref[5.4.88]); @deva[अह] (@ref[5.4.91]).

@note[type=@[vārtika]] @deva[अनुवाकः], @deva[शंयुवाकः], @deva[सूक्तवाकः] = masc.

@deva[अञ्] and @deva[ठञ्] are ordained after @deva[दिक्पूर्वपद] + @deva[अर्ध] when denoting @deva[ग्राम]/@deva[जनपद]]-@deva[विभाग], superseding @deva[यत्] from @ref[4.3.5]–@ref[4.3.6].

Examples: @deva[पौर्वार्धाः], @deva[पौर्वार्धिकाः]; @deva[दाक्षिणार्धाः], @deva[दाक्षिणार्धिकाः].

Derivation: @deva[पौर्वार्धाः] = @deva[ग्रामस्य पूर्वस्मिन् अर्धे भवाः]—a @deva[तद्धितार्थसमास]. The @deva[अनुवृत्ति] of @deva[दिक्पूर्वपदात्] continues from @ref[4.3.6].

@deva[अ] is ordained after @deva[मध्य] in @deva[साम्प्रतिक] (propriety/fitness) sense.

Examples: @deva[मध्यं काष्ठम्], @deva[मध्ये वैयाकरणः], @deva[मध्या स्त्री].

@deva[साम्प्रतिक] = @deva[सम्यक् प्राप्तम्], denoting appropriateness or moderation, distinct from spatial @deva[मध्य] (middle location).

@deva[यञ्] is ordained after @deva[द्वीप] in @deva[अनुसमुद्र] sense, superseding @deva[अण्]/@deva[वुञ्]] from @deva[कच्छादि] (@ref[4.2.133]) and @ref[4.2.134].

Example: @deva[द्वैप्यम्]. Cf. @deva[द्वैप्यं भवन्तोऽनुचरन्ति चक्रम्].

Non-@deva[अनुसमुद्र]: @deva[द्वैपकम्], @deva[द्वैपम्]. @deva[अनुसमुद्र] = @deva[अव्ययीभाव] by @ref[2.1.15].

@deva[ठञ्] is ordained after @deva[कालवाचिन्] words in @deva[शेष] senses, superseding @deva[अण्] and @deva[छ] (@ref[4.2.114]).

Examples: @deva[मासिकः], @deva[आर्धमासिकः], @deva[सांवत्सरिकः]; @deva[कादम्बपुष्पिकम्], @deva[व्रैहिपलालिकम्] (indirect time-denotation).

@deva[कालात्] governs @ref[4.3.11]–@ref[4.3.25] as @deva[अधिकार].

standard:
The affix @deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[शरद्] when denoting @deva[श्राद्ध] (funeral oblation), debarring @deva[अण्] from @ref[4.3.16].

Example: @deva[शारदिकं श्राद्धम्] (the autumnal @deva[श्राद्ध]).

@deva[श्राद्धे] means the funeral rite, not @deva[श्रद्धावान् पुरुषः] (a faithful person). When not @deva[श्राद्ध]-related: @deva[शारदम्].

advanced:
@deva[ठञ्] is ordained after @deva[शरद्] in @deva[श्राद्ध]-sense, superseding @deva[ऋतु]-governed @deva[अण्] (@ref[4.3.16]).

Example: @deva[शारदिकं श्राद्धम्].

@deva[श्राद्धे] = @deva[श्राद्धकर्मणि], not @deva[श्रद्धायुक्ते]. Non-@deva[श्राद्ध] sense: @deva[शारदम्].

standard:
After @deva[सायम्], @deva[चिरम्], @deva[प्राह्णे], @deva[प्रगे], and @deva[कालवाचिन्] indeclinables, @deva[ट्यु] and @deva[ट्युल्] apply with @deva[तुट्]-@deva[आगम].

Examples: @deva[सायंतनम्] (@ref[7.1.1]), @deva[चिरंतनम्], @deva[प्राह्णेतनम्], @deva[प्रगेतनम्]; @deva[दोषातनम्], @deva[दिवातनम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[त्न] after @deva[चिर], @deva[परुत्], @deva[परारि]: @deva[चिरत्नम्], @deva[परुत्नम्], @deva[परारित्नम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: In @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[ग]-@deva[लोप] in @deva[प्रग] before @deva[त्न]: @deva[प्रत्नम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[डिमच्] after @deva[अग्र], @deva[आदि], @deva[पश्चाद्], @deva[अन्त]: @deva[अग्रिमम्], @deva[आदिमम्], @deva[पश्चिमम्], @deva[अन्तिमम्].

@deva[ट्यु]/@deva[ट्युल्]] difference is @deva[स्वर]: @deva[सायन्तन] vs. @deva[सायन्तन].

advanced:
@deva[ट्यु]/@deva[ट्युल्]] with @deva[तुट्]-@deva[आगम] apply after @deva[सायम्], @deva[चिरम्], @deva[प्राह्णे], @deva[प्रगे], and @deva[कालवाचिन्] @deva[अव्यय]s.

Examples: @deva[सायंतनम्], @deva[चिरंतनम्], @deva[प्राह्णेतनम्], @deva[प्रगेतनम्], @deva[दोषातनम्], @deva[दिवातनम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[चिरपरुत्परारिभ्यस्त्नः]—@deva[चिरत्नम्], @deva[परुत्नम्], @deva[परारित्नम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[प्रगो गलोपश्छन्दसि त्नि]—@deva[प्रत्नम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अग्राद्यादिपश्चादन्तेभ्यो डिमच्]—@deva[अग्रिमम्], @deva[आदिमम्], @deva[पश्चिमम्], @deva[अन्तिमम्].

@deva[ट्यु]/@deva[ट्युल्]] are @deva[स्वरभेद]: @deva[सायन्तन]/@deva[सायन्तन]].

standard:
The affix @deva[अ] also applies after @deva[अमावास्या] in @deva[जात]-sense, adding to @deva[वुञ्] (@ref[4.3.30]) and @deva[अण्].

Three forms: @deva[अमावास्यः] (with @deva[अ]), @deva[अमावास्यकः] (with @deva[वुञ्]), @deva[आमावास्यः] (with @deva[अण्]).

@deva[अमावस्य] variant: @deva[अमावस्यः], @deva[अमावस्यकः], @deva[आमावस्यः].

The @deva[जात]-affix undergoes @deva[लुक्] after asterisms @deva[श्रविष्ठा], @deva[फाल्गुनी], @deva[अनुराधा], @deva[स्वाति], @deva[तिष्य], @deva[पुनर्वसु], @deva[हस्त], @deva[विशाखा], @deva[आषाढा], @deva[बहुला]. Feminine affixes also elide by @ref[1.2.49].

Examples: @deva[श्रविष्ठः], @deva[फल्गुनः], @deva[अनुराधः], @deva[स्वातिः], @deva[तिष्यः], @deva[पुनर्वसुः], @deva[हस्तः], @deva[विशाखः], @deva[आषाढः], @deva[बहुलः]. @deva[बहुला] = @deva[कृत्तिका].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[लुक्] after @deva[चित्रा], @deva[रेवती], @deva[रोहिणी] in feminine: @deva[चित्रा], @deva[रेवती], @deva[रोहिणी]. The @deva[स्त्री]-@deva[प्रत्यय] for @deva[रेवती]/@deva[रोहिणी]] (@deva[गौरादि]) is reordained by @ref[4.1.41].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[ट]/@deva[अन्]] after @deva[फल्गुनी]/@deva[आषाढा]] (feminine): @deva[फल्गुनी] (@ref[4.1.15]), @deva[आषाढा].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[छण्] after @deva[श्रविष्ठा]/@deva[आषाढा]]: @deva[श्राविष्ठीयः], @deva[आषाढीयः].

advanced:
@deva[लुक्] applies to @deva[जात]-@deva[प्रत्यय] after @deva[श्रविष्ठादि] asterisms; @deva[स्त्री]-@deva[प्रत्यय] also elides (@ref[1.2.49]).

Forms: @deva[श्रविष्ठः], @deva[फल्गुनः], @deva[अनुराधः], @deva[स्वातिः], @deva[तिष्यः], @deva[पुनर्वसुः], @deva[हस्तः], @deva[विशाखः], @deva[आषाढः], @deva[बहुलः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[चित्रारेवतीरोहिणीभ्यश्च स्त्रियाम्]—@deva[चित्रा], @deva[रेवती], @deva[रोहिणी]. @ref[4.1.41] restores @deva[स्त्री]-@deva[प्रत्यय] for @deva[गौरादि].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[फल्गुन्याषाढाभ्यां टनौ स्त्रियाम्]—@deva[फल्गुनी], @deva[आषाढा].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[श्रविष्ठाषाढाभ्यां छण्]—@deva[श्राविष्ठीयः], @deva[आषाढीयः].

simple:
After a @deva[प्रातिपदिक] (nominal stem) or a word ending in feminine affixes @deva[ङीप्] or @deva[आप्], in the locative case, an affix comes in the sense of 'adapted therein' (@deva[संभूत]).

@deva[संभूत] here does not mean 'birth' or 'existence' (those are covered by @deva[जात] and @deva[भव]). It means 'suitableness' or 'adequacy' (@deva[अवक्लृप्ति], @deva[प्रमाणातिरेक]).

Example: @deva[स्रुघ्ने संभवति] = @deva[स्रौघ्नः] (what is suited to Srughna). Similarly @deva[माथुरः], @deva[राष्ट्रियः].

standard:
The affix @deva[वुञ्] applies after @deva[आश्वयुजी] in @deva[उप्त] sense, debarring @deva[ठञ्].

Example: @deva[आश्वयुज्यां उप्ताः] → @deva[आश्वयुजका माषाः] (pulse sown in @[āśvayujī]).

@deva[आश्वयुजी] = full-moon in @[aśvinī] asterism. @deva[अश्वयुज्] = @deva[अश्विनी]; variant @deva[अश्वनी].

simple:
The affix @deva[वुञ्] comes in the sense of 'debt then due' after @deva[कलापिन्], @deva[अश्वत्थ], and @deva[यवबुस्], which are words that indirectly denote time.

@deva[कलापी] (peacock) = the mating/rainy season when peacocks display. @deva[अश्वत्थ] (sacred fig tree) = the time of its fruiting. @deva[यवबुस्] (barley chaff) = the time of threshing.

Examples: @deva[कलापिनि काले देयम् ऋणम्] = @deva[कलापकम्] (debt due in peacock-mating season), @deva[अश्वत्थकम्], @deva[यवबुसकम्].

standard:
The affix @deva[वुञ्] applies after @deva[कलापिन्], @deva[अश्वत्थ], @deva[यवबुस्] in @deva[ऋण]-@deva[देय] sense. These words denote time indirectly.

@deva[कलापी] = peacock-mating season; @deva[अश्वत्थ] = fig-fruiting season; @deva[यवबुस्] = barley-threshing time.

Examples: @deva[कलापकम्], @deva[अश्वत्थकम्], @deva[यवबुसकम्].

The affix @deva[वुञ्] applies after @deva[ग्रीष्म] and @deva[अवरसम] in @deva[ऋण]-@deva[देय] sense, debarring @deva[अण्]/@deva[ठञ्]].

Examples: @deva[ग्रैष्मकम्], @deva[आवरसमकम्].

@deva[वुञ्] (not @deva[वुन्]) causes @deva[वृद्धि]. @deva[समा] = @deva[वर्ष]. @deva[आवरसमकम्] = @deva[आगामिनां संवत्सराणाम् आद्यवत्सरे देयम्] or @deva[अतीते वत्सरे देयं यद्यपि न दत्तम्].

simple:
The affix @deva[ठञ्] (as well as @deva[वुञ्]) comes after @deva[संवत्सर] (year) and @deva[आग्रहायणी] (a month name) in the sense of 'debt due'.

Examples: @deva[संवत्सरे देयम् ऋणम्] = @deva[सांवत्सरिकम्] (with @deva[ठञ्]) or @deva[सांवत्सरकम्] (with @deva[वुञ्]). Similarly @deva[आग्रहायणिकम्] or @deva[आग्रहायणकम्].

@deva[संवत्सर] is in the @deva[संधिवेलादि] class (@ref[4.3.16]) and takes @deva[अण्] for 'fruit' or 'festival'. This rule ordains @deva[ठञ्] for 'debt'.

standard:
Both @deva[ठञ्] and @deva[वुञ्] apply after @deva[संवत्सर] and @deva[आग्रहायणी] in @deva[ऋण]-@deva[देय] sense.

Examples: @deva[सांवत्सरिकम्] / @deva[सांवत्सरकम्]; @deva[आग्रहायणिकम्] / @deva[आग्रहायणकम्].

@deva[संवत्सर] ∈ @deva[संधिवेलादि] (@ref[4.3.16]) takes @deva[अण्] for @deva[फल]/@deva[पर्व]]; @deva[ठञ्] applies for @deva[ऋण].

simple:
An affix comes after a word denoting time in the @deva[प्रथमा] (nominative) case (1st), in the sense of 'this is his habit or endurance' (@deva[तत् सोढम्]).

@deva[सोढम्] = endured or habituated (@deva[जितम्], @deva[अभ्यस्तम्]).

Example: @deva[निशा सहचरितम् अध्ययनम्] (studying practiced at night) + 'that is his endurance' = @deva[नैशः] or @deva[नैशिकः] @deva[छात्रः] (a student habituated to night study). Similarly @deva[प्रादोषिकः] or @deva[प्रादोषः].

standard:
An affix applies after @deva[कालवाचिन्] (@deva[प्रथमान्त]) in @deva[तत्सोढम्] sense (habituated to that time).

@deva[सोढम्] = @deva[जितम्]/@deva[अभ्यस्तम्]].

Example: @deva[निशा सहचरितम् अध्ययनं तत्सोढम् अस्य] → @deva[नैशः]/@deva[नैशिकः]] @deva[छात्रः]. Similarly @deva[प्रादोषिकः]/@deva[प्रादोषः]].

The affix @deva[ञ्य] applies after @deva[गम्भीर] in @deva[भव] sense, debarring @deva[अण्].

Example: @deva[गाम्भीर्यम्] (profundity).

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: After @deva[बहिस्], @deva[देव], @deva[पञ्चजन]: @deva[बाह्यम्], @deva[दैव्यम्], @deva[पाञ्चजन्यम्]. @deva[बहिस्]-@deva[अन्त्यलोप] per @ref[4.1.85]-@deva[वार्त्तिक].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[ञ्य] after @deva[चतुर्मास] in @deva[यज्ञ]-sense: @deva[चातुर्मास्यानि व्रतानि]; else @deva[चातुर्मासः].

advanced:
@deva[ञ्य] applies after @deva[गम्भीर] in @deva[भव] sense, superseding @deva[अण्].

Example: @deva[गाम्भीर्यम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[बहिर्देवपञ्चजनेभ्यश्च]—@deva[बाह्यम्], @deva[दैव्यम्], @deva[पाञ्चजन्यम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[चतुर्मासाद्यज्ञे]—@deva[चातुर्मास्यानि]; else @deva[चातुर्मासः].

standard:
The affix @deva[ञ्य] applies after @deva[अव्ययीभाव] compounds in @deva[भव] sense, limited to @deva[परिमुखादि], debarring @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[पारिमुख्यम्], @deva[पारिहनव्यम्]. Not @deva[औपकुलम्] (non-@deva[परिमुखादि]).

@deva[परिमुखादि]: @deva[परिमुख], @deva[परिहनु], @deva[पर्योष्ठ], @deva[पर्युलूख], @deva[औपमूल], @deva[खल], @deva[परिसीर], @deva[अनुसीर], @deva[उपसीर], @deva[उपस्थल], @deva[उपकलाप], @deva[अनुपथ], @deva[अनुखड्ग], @deva[अनुतिल], @deva[अनुशीत], @deva[अनुमाष], @deva[अनुयव], @deva[अनुयूप], @deva[अनुवंश], @deva[अनुगङ्गम्], @deva[प्रतिशाख], @deva[अनुसाय].

advanced:
@deva[ञ्य] applies after @deva[अव्ययीभाव] (@deva[परिमुखादि]) in @deva[भव] sense, superseding @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[पारिमुख्यम्], @deva[पारिहनव्यम्]. Non-@deva[परिमुखादि]: @deva[औपकुलम्].

@deva[परिमुखादि] @[gaṇa] lists 22 items.

standard:
The affix @deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[अन्तर्]-prefixed @deva[अव्ययीभाव] in @deva[भव] sense, debarring @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[आन्तर्वेश्मिकम्], @deva[आन्तर्गेहिकम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[ठञ्] after @deva[समान]/@deva[समानादि]]: @deva[सामानिकम्], @deva[सामानग्रामिकम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अध्यात्मादि] (@deva[आकृतिगण]): @deva[आध्यात्मिकम्], @deva[आधिदैविकम्], @deva[आधिभौतिकम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[ऊर्ध्वदम]/@deva[ऊर्ध्वदेह]]: @deva[और्ध्वदमिकः], @deva[और्ध्वदेहिकम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[लोकोत्तरपद]: @deva[ऐहलौकिकम्], @deva[पारलौकिकम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[मुखपार्श्वतसोरीयः]: @deva[मुखतीयम्], @deva[पार्श्वतीयम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[जनपरयोः कुक्]: @deva[जनकीयम्], @deva[परकीयम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[मध्यस्य ईय/मण्/मीय/दिनण्]: @deva[मध्यीयः], @deva[माध्यमम्], @deva[माध्यमीयम्], @deva[माध्यन्दिनम्].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[स्थाम्नो लुक्]: @deva[अश्वत्थामा].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अजिनान्ताल्लुक्]: @deva[वृकाजिनः], @deva[सिंहाजिनः].

advanced:
@deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[अन्तर्]-@deva[अव्ययीभाव] in @deva[भव] sense, superseding @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[आन्तर्वेश्मिकम्], @deva[आन्तर्गेहिकम्].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[समानाद्ठञ्], @deva[तदादेश्च]; @deva[अध्यात्मादिषु] (@deva[आकृतिगण]); @deva[ऊर्ध्वदमाच्च देहाच्च]; @deva[लोकोत्तरपदस्य च]; @deva[मुखपार्श्वतसोरीयः]; @deva[कुग्जनस्य परस्य च]; @deva[मध्यस्य ईय/मण्/मीय/दिनण्]; @deva[स्थाम्नो लुक्]; @deva[अजिनान्ताल्लुक्].

standard:
The affix @deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[क्रतु]/@deva[यज्ञ]]-related @deva[व्याख्यातव्यनामन्] in @deva[भव]/@deva[व्याख्यान]] senses, debarring @deva[अण्].

@deva[क्रतु] (Soma): @deva[अग्निष्टोमिकः], @deva[वाजपेयिकः], @deva[राजसूयिकः]. @deva[यज्ञ] (non-Soma): @deva[पाकयज्ञिकः], @deva[नावयज्ञिकः], @deva[पाञ्चौदनिकः].

Scope: non-@deva[अन्तोदात्त] words (@deva[वाजपेय]/@deva[राजसूय]] = middle accent). @deva[यज्ञ] separate mention includes non-Soma @deva[यज्ञ]s. Plural prevents @deva[स्वरूपविधि] (@ref[1.1.68]).

advanced:
@deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[क्रतु]/@deva[यज्ञ]]-@deva[व्याख्यातव्यनामन्] in @deva[भव]/@deva[व्याख्यान]] senses, superseding @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[अग्निष्टोमिकः], @deva[वाजपेयिकः], @deva[राजसूयिकः]; @deva[पाकयज्ञिकः], @deva[पाञ्चौदनिकः].

Scope: non-@deva[अन्तोदात्त]; @deva[यज्ञ]-mention includes non-Soma. Plural blocks @deva[स्वरूपविधि] (@ref[1.1.68]).

standard:
The affix @deva[अण्] applies after @deva[ऋगयनादि] in @deva[भव]/@deva[व्याख्यान]] senses, debarring @deva[ठञ्]/@deva[ठक्]]/@deva[छ]].

Examples: @deva[आर्गयनः], @deva[पादव्याख्यानः], @deva[वास्तुविद्यः].

@deva[अण्]-repetition blocks subsequent @deva[अपवाद] (@deva[बाधकबाधनार्थम्]).

@deva[ऋगयनादि]: @deva[ऋगयन], @deva[पदव्याख्यान], @deva[छन्दोमान], @deva[छन्दोभाषा], @deva[छन्दोविचिति], @deva[न्याय], @deva[पुनरुक्त], @deva[निरुक्त], @deva[व्याकरण], @deva[निगम], @deva[वास्तुविद्या], @deva[क्षत्रविद्या], @deva[अङ्गविद्या], @deva[विद्या], @deva[उत्पात], @deva[उत्पाद], @deva[उद्याव], @deva[संवत्सर], @deva[मुहूर्त], @deva[उपनिषद्], @deva[निमित्त], @deva[शिक्षा], @deva[भिक्षा], @deva[छन्दोविछिति], @deva[व्याय].

The affix @deva[ठक्] applies after @deva[आयस्थान]-denoting words in @deva[ततआगत] sense, debarring @deva[अण्]/@deva[छ]].

@deva[आय] = lord's share; @deva[आयस्थान] = revenue source.

Examples: @deva[शौल्कशालिकम्], @deva[आकरिकम्]. Plural blocks @deva[स्वरूपविधि] (@ref[1.1.68]).

The affix @deva[अण्] applies after @deva[शुण्डिकादि] in @deva[ततआगत] sense, debarring @deva[ठक्].

Examples: @deva[शौण्डिकम्], @deva[कार्कणम्], @deva[औदपानम्].

@deva[अण्]-repetition serves @deva[बाधकबाधनार्थम्] (blocks subsequent overrides).

@deva[शुण्डिकादि]: @deva[शुण्डिक], @deva[कृकण], @deva[स्थण्डिल], @deva[उदपान], @deva[उपल], @deva[तीर्थ], @deva[भूमि], @deva[तृण], @deva[पर्ण].

The affix @deva[ठञ्] applies after @deva[ऋदन्त] @deva[विद्यायोनिसम्बन्ध] words in @deva[ततआगत] sense, debarring @deva[वुञ्].

@deva[विद्या]: @deva[हौतृकम्], @deva[पौतृकम्]. @deva[योनि]: @deva[भ्रातृकम्], @deva[स्वसृकम्], @deva[मातृकम्].

@deva[ऋत्] = short @deva[ऋ]; @deva[त्] for pronunciation. Non-relationship: @deva[सावित्रम्].

After @deva[गोत्रान्त] (patronymic-ending) words, the @deva[ततआगत] affixes are identical to @deva[अङ्क] (mark) affixes (@ref[4.3.126]–@ref[4.3.127]).

@deva[गोत्र] = any descendant-denoting affix. Examples: @deva[औपगवकः] (mark or origin); @deva[कापटवकम्], @deva[नाडायनकम्] (with @deva[वुञ्] @ref[4.3.126]); @deva[बैदः], @deva[गार्गः], @deva[दाक्षः] (with @deva[अण्] @ref[4.3.127]).

@deva[वत्] indicates complete @deva[अतिदेश].

The affix @deva[रूप्य] applies after @deva[हेतु]/@deva[मनुष्य]]-denoting words in @deva[ततआगत] sense.

@deva[हेतु]: @deva[समरूप्यम्] / @deva[समीयम्] (@ref[4.2.138]). @deva[मनुष्य]: @deva[देवदत्तरूप्यम्] / @deva[दैवदत्तम्].

Plural blocks @deva[स्वरूपविधि] (@ref[1.1.68]). Ablative for @deva[हेतु] per @ref[2.3.25].

The affix @deva[मयट्] applies after @deva[हेतुमनुष्य]-denoting words in @deva[ततआगत] sense.

Examples: @deva[सममयम्], @deva[विषममयम्], @deva[देवदत्तमयम्], @deva[यज्ञदत्तमयम्].

@deva[ट्]-indication: feminine @deva[ङीप्] (@ref[4.1.15]): @deva[सममयी]. Separated from @ref[4.3.81] to block @deva[यथासंख्य] (@ref[1.3.10]).

simple:
An affix from @deva[प्राग्दीव्यतः] (@ref[4.1.83]) comes after a word in the ablative case in the sense of 'what appears for the first time there' (@deva[प्रभवति]).

@deva[प्रभवति] means 'manifests for the first time' or 'appears'—not 'originates', since origin is covered by @deva[तत्र जातः] (@ref[4.3.25]). It means @deva[प्रकाशते], @deva[प्रथमतः उपलभ्यते]—where the ultimate source is unknown.

Examples: @deva[हिमवतः प्रभवति] = @deva[हैमवती] (the Ganges, appearing first in the Himalayas), @deva[दारदी] (the Indus, appearing first in Dardistan).

standard:
Affixes from @deva[प्राग्दीव्यतः] (@ref[4.1.83]) apply after @deva[पञ्चम्यन्त] in @deva[प्रभव] sense (first appearance).

@deva[प्रभवति] = @deva[प्रकाशते], @deva[प्रथमतः उपलभ्यते]; distinct from @deva[उत्पत्ति] (@ref[4.3.25] @deva[जात]).

Examples: @deva[हैमवती] (Ganges), @deva[दारदी] (Indus).

advanced:
Affixes apply after @deva[द्वितीयान्त] in @deva[अधिकृत्य कृते ग्रन्थे] sense.

Examples: @deva[सौभद्रः], @deva[किरातार्जुनीयम्]. Condition: @deva[ग्रन्थे].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[आख्यायिकायां बहुलम्]—@deva[वासवदत्ता], @deva[उर्वशी]; counter: @deva[भैमरथी].

standard:
The affix @deva[छ] applies after @deva[शिशुक्रन्द], @deva[यमसभ], @deva[द्वन्द्व], and @deva[इन्द्रजननादि] in @deva[अधिकृत्य ग्रन्थे] sense, debarring @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[शिशुक्रन्दीयः], @deva[यमसभीयः]; @deva[अग्निकाश्यपीयः], @deva[वाक्यपदीयम्]; @deva[इन्द्रजननीयम्].

@deva[इन्द्रजननादि] = @deva[आकृतिगण].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[देवासुरादि]-@deva[द्वन्द्व] takes @deva[अण्]: @deva[दैवासुरम्], @deva[राक्षोसुरम्].

advanced:
@deva[छ] applies after @deva[शिशुक्रन्द]/@deva[यमसभ]]/@deva[द्वन्द्व]]/@deva[इन्द्रजननादि]] in @deva[अधिकृत्य ग्रन्थे] sense, superseding @deva[अण्].

Examples: @deva[शिशुक्रन्दीयः], @deva[अग्निकाश्यपीयः], @deva[इन्द्रजननीयम्]. @deva[इन्द्रजननादि] = @deva[आकृतिगण].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[देवासुरादेरण्]—@deva[दैवासुरम्], @deva[गौणमुख्यम्].

simple:
An affix comes after a word in the @deva[प्रथमा] (nominative) case in the sense of 'this is his dwelling place' (@deva[स अस्य निवासः]).

@deva[स] shows the nominative case of the first word. @deva[अस्य] shows the genitive meaning of the affix. @deva[निवास] means 'dwelling place'—where a person currently lives.

Examples: @deva[स्रुघ्नो निवासो ऽस्य] = @deva[स्रौघ्नः] (a present dweller of Srughna), @deva[माथुरः], @deva[राष्ट्रियः].

standard:
An affix applies after @deva[प्रथमान्त] in @deva[स अस्य निवासः] sense (his current dwelling place).

@deva[स] = nominative; @deva[अस्य] = genitive meaning; @deva[निवास] = where one currently lives.

Examples: @deva[स्रौघ्नः], @deva[माथुरः], @deva[राष्ट्रियः].

advanced:
Affixes apply after @deva[प्रथमान्त] in @deva[स अस्य अभिजनः] sense.

@deva[निवास] ≠ @deva[अभिजन] (current vs. ancestral). Examples: @deva[स्रौघ्नः], @deva[माथुरः].

@deva[योगविभाग]: @deva[अभिजन] alone continues to @ref[4.3.91].

@deva[कुलत्थ] and @deva[ककारोपध] bases take @deva[अण्] (not @deva[ठक्]) in sense @deva[संस्कृतम्].

@deva[अण्] = @deva[अ] with @deva[वृद्धि] by @ref[7.2.117]. Examples: @deva[कौलत्थम्], @deva[तैत्तिडीकम्], @deva[दार्दभकम्].

This @deva[अपवाद] to @ref[4.4.3] blocks @deva[ठक्].

@deva[नौ] and @deva[द्व्यच्] bases take @deva[ठञ्] in sense @deva[तरति].

Examples: @deva[नाविकः], @deva[घटिकः], @deva[प्लविकः], @deva[बाहुकः].

The @deva[ष्] in @deva[ष्ठन्] is external @deva[सन्धि] (@deva[विसर्गसन्धि]), not @deva[इत्]. Without @deva[षित्], feminine is @deva[बाहुका] (not @deva[*बाहुकी] by @ref[4.1.41]).

@deva[कारिका]: @deva[आकर्षात्...षडेते ठगधिकारे] identifies six @deva[षित्] affixes in this @deva[अधिकार]: @ref[4.4.9] (@deva[ष्ठल्]), @ref[4.4.10] (@deva[ष्ठन्]), @ref[4.4.18], @ref[4.4.53], @ref[4.4.74].

@deva[आकर्ष] takes @deva[ष्ठल्] in sense @deva[चरति].

Example: @deva[आकर्षिकः], f. @deva[आकर्षिकी].

@deva[ष्ठल्]: @deva[ल्] is @deva[इत्] for @deva[स्वरितोदात्त] by @ref[6.1.193]. @deva[ष्] is @deva[इत्] (unlike @ref[4.4.7] where @deva[ष्] is @deva[विसर्गसन्धि])—therefore @deva[षित्], triggering @deva[ङीष्] by @ref[4.1.41].

@deva[आकर्ष] = @deva[निकष] (touchstone for gold).

@deva[कुटिलिका] takes @deva[अण्] (not @deva[ठक्]) in sense @deva[हरति].

@deva[कुटिलिका] = crooked movement; also, blacksmith's forge.

Examples: @deva[कौटिलिको मृगः] (deer that leads hunter astray); @deva[कौटिलिकः कर्मारः] (blacksmith who carries coals on forge).

After @deva[क्त्र्यन्त] (@ref[3.3.88]), @deva[मप्] is @deva[नित्य] in sense @deva[निर्वृत्तम्].

Examples: @deva[पक्त्रिमम्], @deva[उप्त्रिमम्] (@ref[6.1.15]), @deva[कृत्रिमम्].

@deva[मप्] is effectively an @deva[आगम] to @deva[क्त्रि]—@deva[क्त्रि] never appears without it.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[भावप्रत्ययान्तादिमप्] — After @deva[भावप्रत्ययान्त], @deva[इमप्] is added: @deva[पाकिमम्] (@deva[पच्] + @deva[घञ्] @ref[3.3.18] + @deva[इमप्]), @deva[त्यागिमम्], @deva[सेकिमम्], @deva[कुट्टिमम्].

standard:
After a @deva[द्वितीया]-ending word, @deva[ठक्] applies in sense @deva[उञ्छति] (gleans).

@deva[उञ्छ] = picking up fallen grains (@deva[कण]).

Examples: @deva[बादरिकः] 'jujube-gleaner', @deva[श्यामाकिकः], @deva[काणिकः].

advanced:
@deva[परिपन्थ] (in @deva[द्वितीया]) takes @deva[ठक्] in senses @deva[तिष्ठति] and @deva[हन्ति] (by @deva[च]).

Example: @deva[पारिपन्थिकः] 'highwayman'.

@deva[परिपन्थं तिष्ठति]: @deva[यः पन्थानं वर्जयित्वा तिष्ठति] or @deva[यो वा पन्थानं व्याप्य तिष्ठति].

@deva[परिपन्थम्] in @[sūtra] is @deva[लौकिकरूपदर्शनार्थ]—@deva[परिपन्थ] (not @deva[परिपन्थिन्]) is the base.

After @deva[माथोत्तरपद] and @deva[पदवी], @deva[अनुपद], @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[धावति].

@deva[माथ] = @deva[मार्ग].

Examples: @deva[दाण्डमाथिकः], @deva[शौल्कमाथिकः], @deva[पादविकः], @deva[आनुपदिकः].

standard:
After @deva[पदोत्तरपद] (compounds with @deva[पद] as second member) in @deva[द्वितीया], @deva[ठक्] applies in sense @deva[गृह्णाति] (takes).

Examples: @deva[पौर्वपदिकः], @deva[औत्तरपदिकः].

@deva[उत्तरपद] is mentioned to exclude @deva[बहुपद] from this rule.

advanced:
After @deva[पदोत्तरपद] (in @deva[द्वितीया]), @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[गृह्णाति].

Examples: @deva[पौर्वपदिकः], @deva[औत्तरपदिकः].

@deva[उत्तरपदग्रहण] is @deva[बहुपदनिवृत्त्यर्थ]—excludes @deva[बहुपद] from the rule.

standard:
After @deva[धर्म] (in @deva[द्वितीया]), @deva[ठक्] applies in sense @deva[चरति] (practices).

Example: @deva[धर्मं चरति] → @deva[धार्मिकः] 'religious'.

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अधर्मं चरति] → @deva[आधार्मिकः] 'irreligious'.

advanced:
@deva[धर्म] (in @deva[द्वितीया]) takes @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[चरति].

Example: @deva[धार्मिकः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अधर्मादपि] — @deva[आधार्मिकः] 'irreligious'.

@deva[परिषद्] takes @deva[ण्य] (not @deva[ठक्]) in sense @deva[समवैति].

Example: @deva[पारिषद्यः].

@deva[ण्य] = @deva[य] with @deva[वृद्धि] by @ref[7.2.117].

standard:
After a @deva[षष्ठ्यन्त] word, @deva[ठक्] applies in sense @deva[धर्म्यम्] (its customary practice).

@deva[धर्म्य] = customary, relating to established practice.

Examples: @deva[शौल्कशालिकम्] 'custom-house laws', @deva[आकरिकम्], @deva[आपणिकम्], @deva[गौल्मिकम्].

advanced:
After @deva[षष्ठ्यन्त], @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[अवक्रयः] (tax).

Examples: @deva[शौल्कशालिकः], @deva[आपणिकः], @deva[गौल्मिकः], @deva[आकरिकः].

@deva[धर्म्य] (@ref[4.4.47]) vs @deva[अवक्रय]: @deva[धर्म्य] = @deva[धर्मानुकूल विधि]; @deva[अवक्रय] = @deva[कर] (may be @deva[अधार्मिक]).

standard:
After @deva[लवण], @deva[ठञ्] (not @deva[ठक्]) applies in sense @deva[पण्यम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[लावणिकः] 'salt-vendor'.

@deva[ठञ्] vs @deva[ठक्]: accent difference.

advanced:
@deva[लवण] takes @deva[ठञ्] (not @deva[ठक्]) in sense @deva[पण्यम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[लावणिकः].

@deva[ठञ्] vs @deva[ठक्]: @deva[ञित्] vs @deva[कित्] accent.

@deva[शलालु] optionally takes @deva[ष्ठन्] (otherwise @deva[ठक्]) in sense @deva[पण्यम् अस्य].

@deva[ष्ठन्]: @deva[शलालुकः] f. @deva[शलालुकी]
@deva[ठक्]: @deva[शालालुकः] f. @deva[शालालुकी]

standard:
After @deva[परश्वध] (axe), both @deva[ठञ्] and @deva[ठक्] apply in sense @deva[प्रहरणम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[पारश्वधिकः] (by either affix, different accent).

@deva[ठञ्] vs @deva[ठक्]: accent difference.

advanced:
@deva[परश्वध] takes @deva[ठञ्] or @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[प्रहरणम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[पारश्वधिकः].

@deva[ठञ्] vs @deva[ठक्]: @deva[ञित्] vs @deva[कित्] accent.

After @deva[प्रथमान्त], @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[शीलम् अस्य].

Examples: @deva[आपूपिकः], @deva[शाष्कुलिकः], @deva[मौदकिकः].

@deva[भक्षण] and @deva[शील] are both understood in the @deva[प्रत्ययार्थ].

standard:
After @deva[छत्रादि], @deva[ण] (not @deva[ठक्]) applies in sense @deva[शीलम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[छात्रः] 'pupil' (@deva[छत्र] + @deva[ण], lit. 'whose habit is @deva[छदन]—covering the teacher's faults').

@[patañjali]: @deva[गुरुश्छत्रवद् गुरुणा शिष्यश्छत्रवत् छाद्यः] 'teacher covers pupil like umbrella'; or @deva[शिष्येण च गुरुश्छत्रवत् परिपाल्यः] 'pupil protects teacher like umbrella'.

@deva[स्था] requires @deva[उपसर्ग]: @deva[आस्था], @deva[संस्था], @deva[अवस्था].

@deva[छत्रादि] @[gaṇa] (22): @deva[छत्र], @deva[शिक्षा], @deva[प्ररोह], @deva[स्था], @deva[बुभुक्षा], @deva[चुरा], @deva[तितिक्षा], @deva[उपस्थान], @deva[कृषि], @deva[कर्मन्], @deva[विश्वधा], @deva[तपस्], @deva[सत्य], @deva[अनृत], @deva[विशिखा], @deva[विशिका] (@deva[शिबिका]), @deva[भक्षा], @deva[उदस्थान], @deva[पुरोडा], @deva[विक्षा], @deva[चुक्षा], @deva[मन्द्र].

advanced:
@deva[छत्रादि] takes @deva[ण] in sense @deva[शीलम् अस्य].

Example: @deva[छात्रः] (@deva[छद्] → @deva[छत्र] + @deva[ण]).

@[patañjali] on @deva[छात्र]: @deva[गुरुश्छत्रवद्...छाद्यः] or @deva[शिष्येण...परिपाल्यः].

@deva[स्था] requires @deva[उपसर्ग].

@deva[छत्रादि] @[gaṇa] (22): @deva[छत्र], @deva[शिक्षा], @deva[प्ररोह] (@deva[पुरोह]), @deva[स्था], @deva[बुभुक्षा], @deva[चुरा], @deva[तितिक्षा], @deva[उपस्थान], @deva[कृषि] (@deva[ऋषि]), @deva[कर्मन्], @deva[विश्वधा], @deva[तपस्], @deva[सत्य], @deva[अनृत], @deva[विशिखा], @deva[विशिका] (@deva[शिबिका]), @deva[भक्षा], @deva[उदस्थान], @deva[पुरोडा], @deva[विक्षा], @deva[चुक्षा], @deva[मन्द्र].

After @deva[देयवाचक] (in @deva[प्रथमा]), @deva[ठक्] in sense @deva[नियुक्तं दीयते] (rightfully given).

@deva[नियुक्त] = @deva[अव्यभिचारेण] (without exception) or @deva[नित्य] (always).

Examples: @deva[आग्रभोजनिकः], @deva[आपूपिकः], @deva[शाष्कुलिकः].

standard:
After @deva[रथ], @deva[युग], @deva[प्रासङ्ग] (in @deva[द्वितीया]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[वहति] (bears).

Examples: @deva[रथ्यः] 'chariot-horse', @deva[युग्यः] 'yoke-ox', @deva[प्रासङ्ग्यः] (trained with break).

@deva[प्रासङ्ग] = training-yoke for colts.

Rule applies to @deva[रथान्त] compounds: @deva[परमरथ्यः].

@deva[तदन्तविधि] applies; no @deva[लुक्] by @ref[4.1.88]: @deva[द्विरथ्यः].

See also @ref[4.3.121], @ref[4.3.123]. @deva[युग्य] by @ref[3.1.121] differs in accent: @deva[अयुग्यम्] (final @deva[उदात्त] when by @deva[यत्] + @ref[6.2.156]).

@deva[युग] here = chariot-part, not time-cycle.

advanced:
@deva[रथ], @deva[युग], @deva[प्रासङ्ग] (in @deva[द्वितीया]) take @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[वहति].

Examples: @deva[रथ्यः], @deva[युग्यः], @deva[प्रासङ्ग्यः].

@deva[तदन्तविधि] applies (@ref[4.3.121]); no @deva[लुक्] by @ref[4.1.88]: @deva[द्विरथ्यः].

@deva[युग्य] by @ref[3.1.121] (@deva[ल्यप्]) vs this @deva[यत्]: accent differs in @deva[नञ्]-compounds (@ref[6.2.156]): @deva[अयुग्यम्] (final acute by @deva[यत्]).

@deva[युग] = @deva[रथावयव], not @deva[कालावच्छेद].

After @deva[द्वितीयान्त], @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[विध्यति] (@deva[अधनुषा]).

Examples: @deva[पद्याः शर्कराः] (@ref[6.3.53]), @deva[ऊरव्याः कण्टकाः].

@deva[अधनुषा]: excludes bow-piercing; by extension, excludes weapon-piercing (@deva[चौरं विध्यति], etc.).

standard:
After @deva[धन] and @deva[गण] (in @deva[द्वितीया]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[लब्धा] (obtainer).

Examples: @deva[धन्यः] 'fortunate', @deva[गण्यः] 'distinguished'.

@deva[लब्धृ] = √@deva[लभ्] + @deva[तृन्] (takes @deva[द्वितीया]).

advanced:
@deva[धन] and @deva[गण] (in @deva[द्वितीया]) take @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[लब्धा].

Examples: @deva[धन्यः], @deva[गण्यः].

@deva[लब्धृ] = √@deva[लभ्] + @deva[तृन्] (@deva[द्वितीयाकर्मक]).

simple:
The affix @deva[यत्] comes after the word @deva[वश] (control/will) in the accusative case, in the sense of 'gone to that'.

Example: @deva[वशं गतः] 'gone under control' → @deva[वश्यः] 'subdued, under control; a dependant, servant'

@deva[वश] = @deva[काम], @deva[इच्छा] (desire, will). @deva[वश्यः] = @deva[परेच्छानुगामी] 'one who follows another's will'.

standard:
After @deva[वश] (in @deva[द्वितीया]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[गतः].

Example: @deva[वशं गतः] → @deva[वश्यः] 'subdued, dependant'.

@deva[वश] = @deva[काम]/[@deva[इच्छा]. @deva[वश्यः] = @deva[परेच्छानुगामी].

advanced:
@deva[वश] (in @deva[द्वितीया]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[गतः].

Example: @deva[वश्यः].

@deva[वश] = @deva[इच्छा]. @deva[वश्यः] = @deva[तां प्राप्तः], @deva[परेच्छानुगामी].

simple:
The affix @deva[यत्] comes after the word @deva[पद] (foot/footprint) in the nominative case, in the sense of 'that in which it is visible'.

Example: @deva[पदं दृश्यम् अस्मिन्] 'footprint is visible in this' → @deva[पद्यः कर्दमः] 'mud (in which footprints can be seen)'

Also: @deva[पद्याः पांसवः] 'dust (showing footprints)', @deva[पद्यः] 'footpath'

@deva[पद्य] describes mud that is neither too hard nor too fluid—having enough consistency to show footprints.

@deva[दृश्यम्] = @deva[शक्यते द्रष्टुम्] (can be seen), with @deva[कृत्य] affix @deva[य] on √@deva[दृश्].

standard:
After @deva[पद] (in @deva[प्रथमा]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[दृश्यम् अस्मिन्] (visible in it).

Examples: @deva[पद्यः कर्दमः] 'mud showing footprints', @deva[पद्याः पांसवः] 'footprint-showing dust', @deva[पद्यः] 'footpath'.

@deva[पद्य] = mud of medium consistency (neither hard nor fluid).

@deva[दृश्यम्] = @deva[शक्यते द्रष्टुम्] (@deva[कृत्य] sense).

advanced:
@deva[पद] (in @deva[प्रथमा]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[दृश्यम् अस्मिन्].

Examples: @deva[पद्यः कर्दमः], @deva[पद्याः पांसवः], @deva[पद्यः] (footpath).

@deva[दृश्यम्] = @deva[शक्यते द्रष्टुम्] (@deva[कृत्य]-@deva[यत्]).

standard:
After @deva[मूल] (in @deva[प्रथमा]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[आबर्हि] (uprooted).

@deva[आबर्हि] = @deva[उत्पाटनम्] (from √@deva[बृह्]).

Example: @deva[मूलम् एषाम् आबर्हि] → @deva[मूल्याः] 'pulse' (@deva[माषाः], @deva[मुद्गाः])—cereals requiring uprooting.

@deva[पदमञ्जरी]: @deva[आवर्हि] (with @deva[व]), not @deva[आबर्हि].

advanced:
@deva[मूल] (in @deva[प्रथमा]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[आबर्हि].

@deva[आबर्हि] = @deva[उत्पाटनम्] (√@deva[वृहू]).

Example: @deva[मूल्याः] (@deva[माषाः], @deva[मुद्गाः]).

@deva[पदमञ्जरी]: @deva[आवर्हि] preferred over @deva[आबर्हि].

@deva[गृहपति] (in @deva[तृतीया]) takes @deva[ञ्य] in sense @deva[संयुक्तः]. @deva[संज्ञायाम्].

Example: @deva[गार्हपत्यः] (specific @deva[अग्निसंज्ञा]).

Meaning: @deva[अग्नि] in which @deva[गृहपति] + @deva[पत्नी] perform @deva[यज्ञ]; or @deva[गृहपतिमन्त्राध्ययनाग्नि]. Not @deva[दक्षिणाग्नि].

standard:
After @deva[छन्दस्] (in @deva[तृतीया]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[निर्मितम्] (made).

Example: @deva[छन्दसा निर्मितम्] → @deva[छन्दस्यः] 'made at will'.

@deva[छन्दस्] = @deva[इच्छा] (will/desire), not metre or Veda.

advanced:
@deva[छन्दस्] (in @deva[तृतीया]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[निर्मितम्].

Example: @deva[छन्दस्यः].

@deva[छन्दस्] = @deva[इच्छा], not @deva[वेद]/[@deva[वृत्त].

@deva[हृदय] (in @deva[षष्ठी]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[प्रियः]. @deva[संज्ञायाम्] (@ref[4.4.89]).

Example: @deva[हृद्यः].

Restricted use: @deva[हृद्यः देशः], @deva[हृद्यं वनम्]—not @deva[*हृद्यः पुत्रः].

standard:
After @deva[हृदय] (in @deva[षष्ठी]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[बन्धनम् ऋषिः] (hymn that binds).

Example: @deva[हृदयस्य बन्धनम् ऋषिः] → @deva[हृद्यः] 'enchantment mantra' (@deva[वशीकरणमन्त्र]).

@deva[ऋषि] = Vedic hymn/mantra. @deva[बन्धन] = that which binds.

advanced:
@deva[हृदय] (in @deva[षष्ठी]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[बन्धनम् ऋषिः].

Example: @deva[हृद्यः] = @deva[वशीकरणमन्त्रः].

@deva[ऋषि] = @deva[वेदमन्त्र]. @deva[बन्धन] = @deva[येन बध्यते तत्].

@deva[यत्] after @deva[षष्ठ्यन्त] with specific senses:

1. @deva[मत] + @deva[करणम्] → @deva[मत्यः]
2. @deva[जन] + @deva[जल्पः] → @deva[जन्यः]
3. @deva[हल] + @deva[कर्षः] → @deva[हल्यः]

@deva[तदन्तविधि]: @deva[द्विहल्यः], @deva[त्रिहल्यः].

standard:
After @deva[समानतीर्थ] (in @deva[सप्तमी]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[वासी] (resident). @deva[साधुः]-@deva[अनुवृत्ति] ceases.

@deva[तीर्थ] = @deva[गुरु] (preceptor).

Example: @deva[समाने तीर्थे वासी] → @deva[सतीर्थ्यः] 'fellow-student' (@ref[6.3.87]).

advanced:
@deva[समानतीर्थ] (in @deva[सप्तमी]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[वासी]. @deva[साधु]-@deva[अनुवृत्ति] ceases.

@deva[तीर्थ] = @deva[गुरु].

Example: @deva[सतीर्थ्यः] (@ref[6.3.87]).

standard:
After @deva[समानोदर] (in @deva[सप्तमी]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[शयितः] (slept/remained). @deva[उदात्त] on @deva[ओ].

@deva[शयित] = @deva[स्थितः].

Example: @deva[समानोदरे शयितः] → @deva[समानोदर्यः] 'uterine brother' (@ref[6.3.88]).

After @deva[सोदर] (in @deva[सप्तमी]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[शयितः].

@ref[6.3.88]: @deva[समान] optionally → @deva[स] before @deva[उदर] when @deva[यत्] follows.

Example: @deva[सोदर्यः] 'uterine brother' (@deva[य]-@deva[उदात्त], not @deva[ओ]-@deva[उदात्त] as in @ref[4.4.108]).

advanced:
@deva[सोदर] (in @deva[सप्तमी]) takes @deva[यत्] in sense @deva[शयितः].

@ref[6.3.88]: @deva[समान] → @deva[स] optionally.

Example: @deva[सोदर्यः] (@deva[यकारोदात्त]).

@deva[सगर्भ], @deva[सयूथ], @deva[सनुत] take @deva[यन्] in sense @deva[भवः]. Accent differs from @deva[यत्] (@ref[6.1.197]).

Examples: @deva[सगर्भ्यः], @deva[सयूथ्यः], @deva[सनुत्यः] (@deva[ऋग्वेद] II.31.9).

@deva[समान] → @deva[स] in @deva[छन्दस्] (@ref[6.3.84]).

standard:
In @deva[छन्दस्], after @deva[तुग्र], @deva[घन्] applies in sense @deva[भवः].

Examples: @deva[तुग्रियः] (@deva[त्वमग्रे वृषभः तुग्रियाणाम्]); @deva[तुग्र्य] (@deva[ऋग्वेद] I.34.15: @deva[आवः शमं वृषभं तुग्र्यासु]).

@deva[तुग्र्य] = sunk in waters. @deva[तुग्र] = food, firmament, sacrifice, @deva[वरिष्ठ].

advanced:
@deva[तुग्र] takes @deva[घन्] in @deva[छन्दस्], sense @deva[भवः].

Examples: @deva[तुग्रियः], @deva[तुग्र्य] (@deva[ऋग्वेद] I.34.15).

@deva[तुग्र] = @deva[अन्न], @deva[अन्तरिक्ष], @deva[यज्ञ], @deva[वरिष्ठ].

@deva[अग्र] takes @deva[यत्] in @deva[छन्दस्], sense @deva[भवः].

Example: @deva[अग्र्यम्].

Repetition from @ref[4.4.110] indicates @deva[यत्] not blocked by @deva[घच्]/[@deva[छ] (@ref[4.4.117]).

@deva[समुद्र] and @deva[अभ्र] take @deva[घ] in @deva[छन्दस्], sense @deva[भवः].

Examples: @deva[समुद्रियः], @deva[अभ्रियः].

@deva[अभ्र] (@deva[अल्पाच्तर]) listed second is @deva[अनित्यक्रम].

@deva[दूत] (in @deva[षष्ठी]) takes @deva[यत्] in @deva[छन्दस्], sense @deva[भाग]/[@deva[कर्म].

Example: @deva[दूत्यम्].

Accent: @ref[6.1.213] → @deva[दूत्यम्] (@deva[आद्युदात्त]); actual @deva[पाठ] has @deva[अन्तोदात्त].

standard:
In @deva[छन्दस्], after @deva[रेवती], @deva[जगती], @deva[हविष्य] (in @deva[षष्ठी]), @deva[यत्] applies in sense @deva[प्रशस्य] (praising).

@deva[प्रशस्य] = @deva[प्रशंसन] (√@deva[शंस्] + @deva[क्यप्], @deva[भाव]).

Examples: @deva[रेवत्यम्], @deva[जगत्यम्], @deva[हविष्यम्].

@deva[हविष्यम्] derivation: @deva[हविषे हिता] = @deva[हविष्याः] (@ref[5.1.4]); @deva[हविष्यानां प्रशंसनम्] = @deva[हविष्यम्] (this @[sūtra]) with @deva[अ]-@deva[लोप] (@ref[6.4.148]) and @deva[य]-@deva[लोप] (@ref[8.4.64]).

advanced:
@deva[रेवती], @deva[जगती], @deva[हविष्य] (in @deva[षष्ठी]) take @deva[यत्] in @deva[छन्दस्], sense @deva[प्रशस्य].

Examples: @deva[रेवत्यम्], @deva[जगत्यम्], @deva[हविष्यम्].

@deva[हविष्यम्]: @deva[हविष्य] (@ref[5.1.4]) + @deva[यत्] → @deva[हविष्य्] (@ref[6.4.148]) + @deva[यत्] → @deva[हविष्यम्] (@ref[8.4.64]).

simple:
In the Vedas, the affix @deva[अण्] (instead of @deva[यत्]) comes after the word @deva[असुर] in the genitive case, in the sense of 'glamour/magic'.

Example: @deva[असुरस्य माया] 'the magic of Asuras' → @deva[आसुरी] (feminine) as in:
@deva[आसुरी माया स्वधया कृतासि] 'You are made by @[āsurī] (demonic) magic with self-power'

In the Vedas, the affix @deva[यत्] comes after a @deva[प्रातिपदिक] (nominal stem) ending in @deva[मतुप्], when it denotes a mantra used in putting up (@deva[उपधान]) sacrificial bricks (@deva[इष्टका]). When @deva[यत्] is added, the @deva[मतुप्] affix is elided.

Example: @deva[वर्चस्वान्] is a mantra containing @deva[वर्चस्]. Bricks put up with recitation of this mantra are called @deva[वर्चस्या]:

@deva[वर्चस्वत्] + @deva[यत्] → @deva[वर्चस्] + @deva[यत्] (@deva[मतुप्] elided) → @deva[वर्चस्या] (f.)

advanced:
@deva[मूर्धन्वत्] takes @deva[मतुप्] in @deva[छन्दस्] for @deva[वयस्या] bricks.

@deva[वयस्या] and @deva[मूर्धन्वत्या] denote same object. @deva[मूर्धन्] alone → @deva[मूर्धन्याः].

@ref[6.1.176].

standard:
In @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[यत्] with @deva[मत्वर्थ] comes after @deva[प्रथमान्त] when result means @deva[मास] (month) or @deva[तनु] (body). Supersedes @deva[मतुप्].

Months: @deva[नभस्यः] (@[śrāvaṇa]), @deva[सहस्यः] (@[pauṣa]), @deva[तपस्यः] (@[phālguna]), @deva[मधव्यः] (@[vaiśākha]).

Body: @deva[ओजस्या तनूः].

Condition: @deva[मास]/[@deva[तनु] sense. Otherwise @deva[मतुप्]: @deva[मधुमता पात्रेण].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: Optional @deva[यत्] for 'immediately after': @deva[माधव्यः]/[@deva[माधवः].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[लुक्] possible; @deva[अ]/[@deva[इ]/[@deva[र] alternatives: @deva[तपः], @deva[इषो मासः], @deva[शुचिर्मासः].

advanced:
@deva[यत्] with @deva[मत्वर्थ] after @deva[प्रथमान्त] in @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[मास]/[@deva[तनु] sense. Supersedes @deva[मतुप्].

Examples: @deva[नभस्यः], @deva[सहस्यः], @deva[तपस्यः], @deva[मधव्यः] (@ref[6.4.146], @ref[6.1.79]); @deva[ओजस्या तनूः].

@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[अनन्तरार्थे विभाषा]: @deva[माधव्यः]/[@deva[माधवः].
@note[type=@[vārtika]]: @deva[लुक्], @deva[अ]/[@deva[इ]/[@deva[र] alternatives.

standard:
In @deva[छन्दस्], after @deva[भग] with @deva[वेशस्]/[@deva[यशस्] as @deva[पूर्वपद], @deva[यल्] applies with @deva[मत्वर्थ].

@deva[ल्] → accent on preceding vowel (@ref[6.1.193]).

Examples: @deva[वेशोभग्यः], @deva[यशोभग्यः].

@deva[वेशोभग] possibly @deva[द्वन्द्व]: @deva[वेशस्] + @deva[भग].

advanced:
@deva[वेशोयशआदिभगान्त] takes @deva[यल्] in @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[मत्वर्थ].

Examples: @deva[वेशोभग्यः], @deva[यशोभग्यः].

@deva[ल्] for @deva[उपोत्तमोदात्त] (@ref[6.1.193]).

@deva[वेशोभग]/[@deva[यशोभग] takes @deva[ख] in @deva[छन्दस्], @deva[मत्वर्थ].

Examples: @deva[वेशोभगीनः], @deva[यशोभगीनः].

Separate @[sūtra]: @deva[यथासंख्यनिवृत्ति]; @deva[ख]-@deva[अनुवृत्ति] to @ref[4.4.133].

simple:
In the Vedas, the affix @deva[यत्] comes after the word @deva[अपस्] (water) in the instrumental case, in the sense of 'sanctified thereby'.

Example: @deva[अप्यम्] 'offering purified with water' as in:
@deva[यस्येदम् अप्यं हविः] 'whose offering is purified with water'

standard:
In @deva[छन्दस्], after @deva[सहस्र] (in @deva[तृतीया]), @deva[घ] applies in sense @deva[संमितः] (equal to).

Example: @deva[सहस्रियः] 'equal to a thousand' (@deva[सहस्रियासो अपां नोर्मयः]; @deva[अयम् अग्निः सहस्रियः]).

@deva[संमित] = @deva[तुल्य]. Variant: @deva[समित].
